eed for the enactment of laws that reflect the continent\u2019s unique identity and serve its people first. \u201cAfrica is in our hands. It is now our collective responsibility to ensure that we&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/muha-calls-for-african-centered-laws\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Muha Calls for African-Centered Laws\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-18214 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"FAREWELL\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/farewell\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/imge-for-presdi-2-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/imge-for-presdi-2-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"imge for presdi\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/farewell\/\" title=\"FAREWELL\" rel=\"bookmark\">FAREWELL<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>FAREWELL Story By: Noreen Sitali As the 7th Parliament prepares to conclude its term on the 19th of March 2025, paving the way for the swearing-in ceremony for members of the 8th Parliament and the election of the Speaker and Deputy Speaker on the 20th of March, ahead of the transition, President Nangolo Mbumba delivered&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/farewell\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about FAREWELL\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-18209 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"SA MP Calls for Implementation of Nama Language Agreement.18 March 2025\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sa-mp-calls-for-implementation-of-nama-language-agreement-18-march-2025\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/DEFAULT-6-copy-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/DEFAULT-6-copy-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"DEFAULT (6) copy\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sa-mp-calls-for-implementation-of-nama-language-agreement-18-march-2025\/\" title=\"SA MP Calls for Implementation of Nama Language Agreement.18 March 2025\" rel=\"bookmark\">SA MP Calls for Implementation of Nama Language Agreement.18 March 2025<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story By: Sakeus Iikela A South African Member of Parliament has called for urgent action to implement a bilateral agreement on preserving the Nama language between Namibia and South Africa.Speaking in Windhoek on Monday, Hon. Newrene Klaaste, Speaker of the Northern Cape Provincial Legislature, warned that without concrete efforts between the two countries, the language&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sa-mp-calls-for-implementation-of-nama-language-agreement-18-march-2025\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about SA MP Calls for Implementation of Nama Language Agreement.18 March 2025\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-18129 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"NAmNet pays courtesy call on Speaker Katjavivi.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namnet-pays-courtesy-call-on-speaker-katjavivi\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/NamNet-600x600.png\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/NamNet-600x600.png 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"NamNet\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namnet-pays-courtesy-call-on-speaker-katjavivi\/\" title=\"NAmNet pays courtesy call on Speaker Katjavivi.\" rel=\"bookmark\">NAmNet pays courtesy call on Speaker Katjavivi.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The Namibian Civil Society Non-State Actors Network (NamNet) has paid a courtesy call on the Speaker of the National Assembly Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi on Thursday.The call was to strengthen ties between Parliament and Civil Society Organisations.Leading the delegation, Ronny Dempers called for an inclusion of civil society in the work of parliament and partnering&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namnet-pays-courtesy-call-on-speaker-katjavivi\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about NAmNet pays courtesy call on Speaker Katjavivi.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-18043 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"COMMONWEALTH DAY 2025\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/commonwealth-day-2025\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/Common-Wealth-1-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/Common-Wealth-1-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Common Wealth 1\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/commonwealth-day-2025\/\" title=\"COMMONWEALTH DAY 2025\" rel=\"bookmark\">COMMONWEALTH DAY 2025<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by Andreas Sheya Namibia joins other members in celebrating Commonwealth Day 2025, which is being celebrated across the 56-member countries. Under this year&#8217;s theme &#8220;Together We Thrive,&#8221; which underscores embodiment of unity, peace, and the strength of these connected communities whereby all members play an active role to empower each other. In his remarks,&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/commonwealth-day-2025\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about COMMONWEALTH DAY 2025\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17920 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Muha reaffirms Namibia\u2019s support for Cuba\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/muha-reaffirms-namibias-support-for-cuba\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/NC-Muha-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/NC-Muha-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"NC Muha\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/muha-reaffirms-namibias-support-for-cuba\/\" title=\"Muha reaffirms Namibia\u2019s support for Cuba\" rel=\"bookmark\">Muha reaffirms Namibia\u2019s support for Cuba<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by\u00a0 Sakeus Iikela Chairperson of the National Council Hon. Lukas Sinimbo Muha has reaffirmed Namibia\u2019s steadfast support for Cuba, amid ongoing tension with the United States of America.While acknowledging Cuba\u2019s invaluable assistance during Namibia\u2019s struggle for Independence, Muha expressed concern over the economic sanctions imposed on Cuba by the new US administration under President&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/muha-reaffirms-namibias-support-for-cuba\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Muha reaffirms Namibia\u2019s support for Cuba\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17875 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"SITTING OF THE PAN AFRICAN PARLIAMENT COMMITTEES AND OTHER ORGANS, 18-28 FEBRUARY 2025\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sitting-of-the-pan-african-parliament-committees-and-other-organs-18-28-february-2025\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/PAP-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/PAP-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"PAP\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">