an-today\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi (right) bidding farewell to outgoing KAS Resident Representative, Natalie Russman today.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17615 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Standing committee on constitution and legal affairs visits Denmark Parliament.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/standing-committee-on-constitution-and-legal-affairs-visits-denmark-parliament\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/Denmark-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/Denmark-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Denmark\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/standing-committee-on-constitution-and-legal-affairs-visits-denmark-parliament\/\" title=\"Standing committee on constitution and legal affairs visits Denmark Parliament.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Standing committee on constitution and legal affairs visits Denmark Parliament.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The Parliamentary Standing Committee on Constitutional and Legal Affairs is on a weeklong benchmark visit to Denmark to engage with the Danish Parliament and key institutions to exchange ideas on access to justice, law reform, human rights protection, anti-corruption efforts, and the conduct of free and fair elections.The delegation will be in that country\u2019s capital&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/standing-committee-on-constitution-and-legal-affairs-visits-denmark-parliament\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Standing committee on constitution and legal affairs visits Denmark Parliament.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17593 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Parliament embraces digital future with e-Parliament strategy.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliament-embraces-digital-future-with-e-parliament-strategy\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/ott-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/ott-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"ott\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliament-embraces-digital-future-with-e-parliament-strategy\/\" title=\"Parliament embraces digital future with e-Parliament strategy.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Parliament embraces digital future with e-Parliament strategy.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Eino Vatileni Parliament, through its e-parliament strategy, is set to modernize its operations with soon to be launched digital tools. The move is aimed at improving transparency, citizen engagement, and parliamentary efficiency ahead of the 8th Parliament.These key initiatives which include a mobile app, online bill register system, and an information communication technology policy framework&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliament-embraces-digital-future-with-e-parliament-strategy\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Parliament embraces digital future with e-Parliament strategy.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17519 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Assembly Welcomes the Removal of Cuba from U.S. Terrorism List .\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-assembly-welcomes-the-removal-of-cuba-from-u-s-terrorism-list\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/01\/cuba-speaker-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/01\/cuba-speaker-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"cuba speaker\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-assembly-welcomes-the-removal-of-cuba-from-u-s-terrorism-list\/\" title=\"National Assembly Welcomes the Removal of Cuba from U.S. Terrorism List .\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Assembly Welcomes the Removal of Cuba from U.S. Terrorism List .<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; Story by Sacky Kadhikwa The National Assembly, under the leadership of Speaker Prof. Peter Katjavivi, wholeheartedly supports the Biden Administration&#8217;s historic decision to remove Cuba from the U.S. Department of State\u2019s list of states sponsoring terrorism. This landmark move signals a positive shift towards restoring diplomatic relations between Cuba and the United States, fostering&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-assembly-welcomes-the-removal-of-cuba-from-u-s-terrorism-list\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Assembly Welcomes the Removal of Cuba from U.S. Terrorism List .\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17463 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter  Katjavivi\u2019s illustrious career highlighted at last SADC-PF Assembly.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-of-the-national-assembly-hon-prof-peter-katjavivis-illustrious-career-highlighted-at-last-sadc-pf-assembly\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/speaker-honored-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/speaker-honored-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"speaker honored\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-of-the-national-assembly-hon-prof-peter-katjavivis-illustrious-career-highlighted-at-last-sadc-pf-assembly\/\" title=\"Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter  Katjavivi\u2019s illustrious career highlighted at last SADC-PF Assembly.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter  Katjavivi\u2019s illustrious career highlighted at last SADC-PF Assembly.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Date: 10\/12\/2024 Livingstone, Zambia &#8211; Speaker of the National Assembly of Zimbabwe, Hon. Adv. Jacob Mudenda, has hailed his Namibian counterpart, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi describing him as a towering figure in efforts to transform the Southern African Development Community Parliamentary Forum (SADC-PF) into a regional parliament. A valedictory ceremony was&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-of-the-national-assembly-hon-prof-peter-katjavivis-illustrious-career-highlighted-at-last-sadc-pf-assembly\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter  Katjavivi\u2019s illustrious career highlighted at last SADC-PF Assembly.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17363 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Namibian lawmakers partake in 45th Annual Forum of Parliamentarians for Global Action in Pakistan\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibian-lawmakers-partake-in-45th-annual-forum-of-parliamentarians-for-global-action-in-pakistan\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/11\/GPA-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/11\/GPA-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"GPA\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibian-lawmakers-partake-in-45th-annual-forum-of-parliamentarians-for-global-action-in-pakistan\/\" title=\"Namibian lawmakers partake in 45th Annual Forum of Parliamentarians for Global Action in Pakistan\" rel=\"bookmark\">Namibian lawmakers partake in 45th Annual Forum of Parliamentarians for Global Action in Pakistan<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Eino Vatileni Namibian parliamentarians alongside other lawmakers from around the world, participated in the 45th Annual Forum of Parliamentarians for Global Action (PGA), held in Islamabad, Pakistan. The forum, held from October 28-29, 2024, also hosted the 13th Consultative Assembly of Parliamentarians on the International Criminal&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibian-lawmakers-partake-in-45th-annual-forum-of-parliamentarians-for-global-action-in-pakistan\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Namibian lawmakers partake in 45th Annual Forum of Parliamentarians for Global Action in Pakistan\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17360 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"APRM country report presented to Speaker.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/aprm-country-report-presented-to-speaker\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/11\/APRM-country-report-presented-to-Speaker-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/11\/APRM-country-report-presented-to-Speaker-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"APRM country report presented to Speaker\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/aprm-country-report-presented-to-speaker\/\" title=\"APRM country report presented to Speaker.\" rel=\"bookmark\">APRM country report presented to Speaker.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The African Peer Review Mechanism (APRM) National Secretariat led by its Chief Executive Officer, Ambassador Lineekela Mboti visited the Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi today, to present the APRM Namibia Country Review Report. Ambasador Mboti informed the Speaker that the APRM Namibia Country Review Report was Namibia\u2019s first peer review report&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/aprm-country-report-presented-to-speaker\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about APRM country report presented to Speaker.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17356 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Deputy Speaker Advocates for Pan-Africanism Revival .\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/deputy-speaker-advocates-for-pan-africanism-revival\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/11\/Loide-Kasingo-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/11\/Loide-Kasingo-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Loide Kasingo\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/deputy-speaker-advocates-for-pan-africanism-revival\/\" title=\"Deputy Speaker Advocates for Pan-Africanism Revival .\" rel=\"bookmark\">Deputy Speaker Advocates for Pan-Africanism Revival .<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Sakeus Iikela Johannesburg, South Africa \u2014 Deputy Speaker of the National Assembly Hon. Loide Kasingo has called on all African countries to introduce national programmes aimed at educating young people on the ideals of Pan-Africanism to strengthen unity and promote development on the continent. Kasingo said this is especially important to ensure that young people&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/deputy-speaker-advocates-for-pan-africanism-revival\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Deputy Speaker Advocates for Pan-Africanism Revival .\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17273 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Namibia highlights achievements at IPU Assembly.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibia-highlights-achievements-at-ipu-assembly\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/sustainability-speaker-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/sustainability-speaker-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"sustainability speaker\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibia-highlights-achievements-at-ipu-assembly\/\" title=\"Namibia highlights achievements at IPU Assembly.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Namibia highlights achievements at IPU Assembly.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Geneva, Switzerland &#8211; Namibia is listed among the 38% of countries that have passed legislation, adopted decisions and\/or taken specific action in follow up to IPU outcomes. This was revealed during the special accountability segment of the General Debate at the IPU Assembly that assesses how parliaments have followed up on&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibia-highlights-achievements-at-ipu-assembly\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Namibia highlights achievements at IPU Assembly.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17269 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Kauma urges Parliaments to legislate for women\u2019s representation.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/kauma-urges-parliaments-to-legislate-for-womens-representation\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/hon-kauma-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/hon-kauma-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"hon kauma\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/kauma-urges-parliaments-to-legislate-for-womens-representation\/\" title=\"Kauma urges Parliaments to legislate for women\u2019s representation.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Kauma urges Parliaments to legislate for women\u2019s representation.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; By Rafael Hangula Geneva \u2013 The Vice-Chairperson of the National Council, Victoria Kauma, has called on national parliaments and member states of the Inter-Parliamentary Union (IPU) to enact laws that will enhance women\u2019s representation. Kauma made this appeal during a debate on gender parity titled \u201cPushing Back on the Pushback: Men and Women MPs&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/kauma-urges-parliaments-to-legislate-for-womens-representation\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Kauma urges Parliaments to legislate for women\u2019s representation.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17244 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker appeals for STI ethical standards in final remarks to IPU Assembly.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-appeals-for-sti-ethical-standards-in-final-remarks-to-ipu-assembly\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/speaker-IPU-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/speaker-IPU-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"speaker IPU\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-appeals-for-sti-ethical-standards-in-final-remarks-to-ipu-assembly\/\" title=\"Speaker appeals for STI ethical standards in final remarks to IPU Assembly.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker appeals for STI ethical standards in final remarks to IPU Assembly.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; Story by George Sanzila Date: 14\/10\/2024 Geneva, Switzerland &#8211; Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi has implored parliaments to enact legislations that establish ethical standards for science, technology and innovation development including ensuring the implementation of such laws. Speaker made this call today in his final speech to hundreds of delegates&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-appeals-for-sti-ethical-standards-in-final-remarks-to-ipu-assembly\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker appeals for STI ethical standards in final remarks to IPU Assembly.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17238 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker honoured for dedicated service .\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-honoured-for-dedicated-service\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-t