27 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker to lead MPs to IPU\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-to-lead-mps-to-ipu\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/IPU-ASSEMBLY-scaled-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/IPU-ASSEMBLY-scaled-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/IPU-ASSEMBLY-scaled-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"\" title=\"IPU ASSEMBLY\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-to-lead-mps-to-ipu\/\" title=\"Speaker to lead MPs to IPU\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker to lead MPs to IPU<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>By George Sanzila Date: 09\/10\/24 Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi will lead a delegation of Members of Parliament to the 149th Inter Parliamentary Union (IPU) Assembly to be held in Geneva, Switzerland from 13 to 17 October 2024. According to a statement released by the world parliamentary body ahead of the&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-to-lead-mps-to-ipu\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker to lead MPs to IPU\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17198 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi  launches late wife\u2019s memoir posthumously.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-hon-prof-peter-katjavivi-launches-late-wifes-memoir-posthumously\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/speaker-oct-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/speaker-oct-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"speaker oct\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-hon-prof-peter-katjavivi-launches-late-wifes-memoir-posthumously\/\" title=\"Speaker Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi  launches late wife\u2019s memoir posthumously.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi  launches late wife\u2019s memoir posthumously.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; Story by George Sanzila Date: 04 October 2024 Windhoek &#8211; Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi has described his late wife Jane Katjavivi as a social justice advocate and a staunch promoter of literature, who dedicated her life to preserving the Namibian heritage. Hon. Katjavivi mentioned this at the launch of&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-hon-prof-peter-katjavivi-launches-late-wifes-memoir-posthumously\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi  launches late wife\u2019s memoir posthumously.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17172 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker opens Namibia Bremen Partnership Exhibition.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-opens-namibia-bremen-partnership-exhibition\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/06-speaker-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/06-speaker-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"06 speaker\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-opens-namibia-bremen-partnership-exhibition\/\" title=\"Speaker opens Namibia Bremen Partnership Exhibition.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker opens Namibia Bremen Partnership Exhibition.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Speaker opens Namibia Bremen Partnership Exhibition. Mayor of the Freie Hansestadt Bremen in German, Dr. Andreas Bovenschulte and his delegation paid a courtesy visit on the Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi today. In the company of Dr. Bovenschulte was his Namibian counterpart, the Mayor of the City of Windhoek, Her Worship&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-opens-namibia-bremen-partnership-exhibition\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker opens Namibia Bremen Partnership Exhibition.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17136 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Muha Criticises UN Security Council Veto Power.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/muha-criticises-un-security-council-veto-power\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/Muha-Criticises-UN-Security-Council-Veto-Power-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/Muha-Criticises-UN-Security-Council-Veto-Power-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Muha Criticises UN Security Council Veto Power\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/muha-criticises-un-security-council-veto-power\/\" title=\"Muha Criticises UN Security Council Veto Power.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Muha Criticises UN Security Council Veto Power.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; Sakeus Iikela Chairperson of the National Council, Hon. Lukas Sinimbo Muha, has called on the international community to reform the United Nations Security Council to ensure that it responds meaningfully to all threats to global peace and security.He particularly criticised the veto power held by the five permanent members of the Security Council calling&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/muha-criticises-un-security-council-veto-power\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Muha Criticises UN Security Council Veto Power.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-17046 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Algerian Ambassador pays courtesy call on Speaker.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/algerian-ambassador-pays-courtesy-call-on-speaker\/\" title=\"Algerian Ambassador pays courtesy call on Speaker.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Algerian Ambassador pays courtesy call on Speaker.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; Story by George Sanzila The Ambassador of the People\u2019s Republic of Algeria, H.E. Abdelkrim Diaf, today (11\/09\/24) paid a courtesy call on the Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi. The two, who recounted historical ties between the two countries established during Namibia\u2019s struggle for independence, discussed several issues of mutual interest&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/algerian-ambassador-pays-courtesy-call-on-speaker\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Algerian Ambassador pays courtesy call on Speaker.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-17039 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Nandi-Ndaitwah urges JNC members to champion education.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/nandi-ndaitwah-urges-jnc-members-to-champion-education\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/NJ-council-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/NJ-council-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"NJ council\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/nandi-ndaitwah-urges-jnc-members-to-champion-education\/\" title=\"Nandi-Ndaitwah urges JNC members to champion education.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Nandi-Ndaitwah urges JNC members to champion education.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Nandi-Ndaitwah urges JNC members to champion education Sakeus Iikela Vice President H.E Dr. Netumbo Nandi-Ndaitwah has called on members of the Junior National Council to lead by example and encourage their peers to stay away from harmful behaviours such as alcohol and drugs, which can negatively impact education.She made these remarks when she officially opened&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/nandi-ndaitwah-urges-jnc-members-to-champion-education\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Nandi-Ndaitwah urges JNC members to champion education.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-17007 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"The Chairperson of the National Council, Hon. Lukas Muha, had the honor of receiving a courtesy call from the Student Representative Council (SRC) of the Durban University of Technology (DUT).\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/the-chairperson-of-the-national-council-hon-lukas-muha-had-the-honor-of-receiving-a-courtesy-call-from-the-student-representative-council-src-of-the-durban-university-of-technology-dut\/\" title=\"The Chairperson of the National Council, Hon. Lukas Muha, had the honor of receiving a courtesy call from the Student Representative Council (SRC) of the Durban University of Technology (DUT).\" rel=\"bookmark\">The Chairperson of the National Council, Hon. Lukas Muha, had the honor of receiving a courtesy call from the Student Representative Council (SRC) of the Durban University of Technology (DUT).<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The Chairperson of the National Council, Hon. Lukas Muha, had the honor of receiving a courtesy call from the Student Representative Council (SRC) of the Durban University of Technology (DUT). During the meeting, Hon. Muha provided a detailed overview of the mandate of the Parliament of Namibia and shared significant insights into the enduring relationship&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/the-chairperson-of-the-national-council-hon-lukas-muha-had-the-honor-of-receiving-a-courtesy-call-from-the-student-representative-council-src-of-the-durban-university-of-technology-dut\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about The Chairperson of the National Council, Hon. Lukas Muha, had the honor of receiving a courtesy call from the Student Representative Council (SRC) of the Durban University of Technology (DUT).\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-16955 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"The Chairperson of the National Council Hon Lukas Muha on Wednesday officially opened the joint National Council and Regional Councils conference in Tsumeb, Oshikoto Region.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/the-chairperson-of-the-national-council-hon-lukas-muha-on-wednesday-officially-opened-the-joint-national-council-and-regional-councils-conference-in-tsumeb-oshikoto-region\/\" title=\"The Chairperson of the National Council Hon Lukas Muha on Wednesday officially opened the joint National Council and Regional Councils conference in Tsumeb, Oshikoto Region.\" rel=\"bookmark\">The Chairperson of the National Council Hon Lukas Muha on Wednesday officially opened the joint National Council and Regional Councils conference in Tsumeb, Oshikoto Region.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Hon Muha opens joint NC conference with Regional Councils The Chairperson of the National Council Hon Lukas Muha on Wednesday officially opened the joint National Council and Regional Councils conference in Tsumeb, Oshikoto Region. This important event will run until Friday, August 30, 2024. Under the theme \u201cHarnessing the Roles and Mandates of the National&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/the-chairperson-of-the-national-council-hon-lukas-muha-on-wednesday-officially-opened-the-joint-national-council-and-regional-councils-conference-in-tsumeb-oshikoto-region\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about The Chairperson of the National Council Hon Lukas Muha on Wednesday officially opened the joint National Council and Regional Councils conference in Tsumeb, Oshikoto Region.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-16930 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker wants strengthened cooperation between China and Africa: 21 August 2024\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-wants-strengthened-cooperation-between-china-and-africa-21-august-2024\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/speaker_china-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/speaker_china-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"speaker_china\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-wants-strengthened-cooperation-between-china-and-africa-21-august-2024\/\" title=\"Speaker wants strengthened cooperation between China and Africa: 21 August 2024\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker wants strengthened cooperation between China and Africa: 21 August 2024<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi has called for a continued mutually beneficial partnership between China and African countries. Hon. Katjaivi mentioned this when he addressed delegates on Wednesday (21\/08\/24) at the commemoration of the 40th anniversary of the National People\u2019s Congress of the People\u2019s Republic&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-wants-strengthened-cooperation-between-china-and-africa-21-august-2024\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker wants strengthened cooperation between China and Africa: 21 August 2024\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-16857 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Parliament wants FIMA pension preservation regulations tabled.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliament-wants-fima-pension-preservation-regulations-tabled\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Story-1-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Story-1-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Story 1\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliament-wants-fima-pension-preservation-regulations-tabled\/\" title=\"Parliament wants FIMA pension preservation regulations tabled.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Parliament wants FIMA pension preservation regulations tabled.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; Story by George Sanzila Date: 09\/08\/2024 Parliament has recommended that the Minister of Finance and Public Enterprises, Hon. Iipumbu Shiimi put on hold the controversial clause relating to the preservation of retirement benefits in the new Financial Institutions and Markets Act, Act. No2 of 2021, and that the regulations concerned be tabled in parliament&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliament-wants-fima-pension-preservation-regulations-tabled\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Parliament wants FIMA pension preservation regulations tabled.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-16751 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"SADC MPs and Experts meet to discuss climate change.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sadc-mps-and-experts-meet-to-discuss-climate-change\/\" title=\"SADC MPs and Experts meet to discuss climate change.\" rel=\"bookmark\">SADC MPs and Experts meet to discuss climate change.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The African Group of Negotiators Experts Support (AGNES) in collaboration with the Parliament of the Republic of Namibia are holding the second Southern Africa Parliamentarian Regional Meeting on strengthening the capacity of national parliaments on oversights in climate action accountability and reporting in Namibia from 31st July \u2013 2nd August 2024. It was officially opened&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sadc-mps-and-experts-meet-to-discuss-climate-change\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about SADC MPs and Experts meet to discuss climate change.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-16739 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Muha calls on Zambia to share experience on CDF with Namibia\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/muha-calls-on-zambia-to-share-experience-on-cdf-with-namibia\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/NC-members-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/NC-members-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"NC members\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/muha-calls-on-zambia-to-share-experience-on-cdf-with-namibia\/\" title=\"Muha calls on Zambia to share experience on CDF with Namibia\" rel=\"bookmark\">Muha calls on Zambia to share experience on CDF with Namibia<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/s-iikelaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Sakeus Iikela Chairperson of the National Council Hon. Lukas Sinimbo Muha says Namibia is exploring the possibility of entering into a cooperation agreement with the Parliament of Zambia to learn more about how that country is implementing the Constituency Development Fund law. Muha said lessons from the implementation of the CDF law in Zambia will&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/muha-calls-on-zambia-to-share-experience-on-cdf-with-namibia\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Muha calls on Zambia to share experience on CDF with Namibia\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-16641 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"President of the Republic of Namibia, H.E. Dr. Nangolo Mbumba is addressing the newly sworn in Members of the 6th session of the Children\u2019s Parliament drawn from schools in all 14 regions of Namibia\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.p