imentary Forum has launched its new Strategic Plan for 2024 \u2013 2028 in Luanda, Angola ahead of the the start of the the forum\u2019s 55th Plenary Asssembly which will be officially opened by Speaker of the Parliament of Angola, Hon. Carolina Cerqueira tommorow, 02 July&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sadc-pf-new-strategic-plan-launched-as-region-gravitates-toward-regional-parliament\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about SADC-PF new Strategic Plan launched as region gravitates toward regional parliament.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-16419 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-latest-added-documents category-news category-159 category-219 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Assembly is gearing up the sixth session of the Children&#8217;s parliament, happening from 12-19 July 2024.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-assembly-is-gearing-up-the-sixth-session-of-the-childrens-parliament-happening-from-12-19-july-2024\/\" title=\"National Assembly is gearing up the sixth session of the Children&#8217;s parliament, happening from 12-19 July 2024.\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Assembly is gearing up the sixth session of the Children&#8217;s parliament, happening from 12-19 July 2024.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/latest-added-documents\/\" >Latest Added Documents<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/p-dumeniparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-assembly-is-gearing-up-the-sixth-session-of-the-childrens-parliament-happening-from-12-19-july-2024\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Assembly is gearing up the sixth session of the Children&#8217;s parliament, happening from 12-19 July 2024.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-16390 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Russia Open to Increasing Scholarship Quota for Namibian Students\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/russia-open-to-increasing-scholarship-quota-for-namibian-students\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/06\/293A4500-scaled-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/06\/293A4500-scaled-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/06\/293A4500-scaled-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"\" title=\"293A4500\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/russia-open-to-increasing-scholarship-quota-for-namibian-students\/\" title=\"Russia Open to Increasing Scholarship Quota for Namibian Students\" rel=\"bookmark\">Russia Open to Increasing Scholarship Quota for Namibian Students<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/s-iikelaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Sakeus Iikela The Russian government has expressed openness to increasing the scholarship quota for Namibian students, particularly in the field of medicine, to further strengthen the relationship between the two countries. This announcement was made by Senator Yelena Perminova, the Chairperson of the Committee on Social Policy and Head of the Friendship Group for Cooperation&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/russia-open-to-increasing-scholarship-quota-for-namibian-students\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Russia Open to Increasing Scholarship Quota for Namibian Students\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-16386 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Namibia-Russia Parliamentary Friendship Group Holds First Meeting\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibia-russia-parliamentary-friendship-group-holds-first-meeting\/\" title=\"Namibia-Russia Parliamentary Friendship Group Holds First Meeting\" rel=\"bookmark\">Namibia-Russia Parliamentary Friendship Group Holds First Meeting<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/s-iikelaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Sakeus Iikela In a historic engagement, the Namibia-Russia Parliamentary Friendship Group held its first meeting in Windhoek to fortify the existing cooperation agreement and chart a future course for inter parliamentary interactions. The meeting was attended by members of the National Council and a delegation of members of the Federation Council of the Federal Assembly&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibia-russia-parliamentary-friendship-group-holds-first-meeting\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Namibia-Russia Parliamentary Friendship Group Holds First Meeting\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-16345 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-latest-added-documents category-news category-159 category-219 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"The Chairperson of the National Council, Hon Lukas Sinimbo Muha, on Monday, welcomed a delegation of MPs from the Federation Council of the Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation, led by Hon. Elena Perminova, Chairperson of the Committee on Social Policy and Head of the Friendship Group for Cooperation.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/the-chairperson-of-the-national-council-hon-lukas-sinimbo-muha-on-monday-welcomed-a-delegation-of-mps-from-the-federation-council-of-the-federal-assembly-of-the-russian-federation-led-by-hon-elen\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/06\/NC-26.06.24-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/06\/NC-26.06.24-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"NC 26.06.24\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/the-chairperson-of-the-national-council-hon-lukas-sinimbo-muha-on-monday-welcomed-a-delegation-of-mps-from-the-federation-council-of-the-federal-assembly-of-the-russian-federation-led-by-hon-elen\/\" title=\"The Chairperson of the National Council, Hon Lukas Sinimbo Muha, on Monday, welcomed a delegation of MPs from the Federation Council of the Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation, led by Hon. Elena Perminova, Chairperson of the Committee on Social Policy and Head of the Friendship Group for Cooperation.\" rel=\"bookmark\">The Chairperson of the National Council, Hon Lukas Sinimbo Muha, on Monday, welcomed a delegation of MPs from the Federation Council of the Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation, led by Hon. Elena Perminova, Chairperson of the Committee on Social Policy and Head of the Friendship Group for Cooperation.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/latest-added-documents\/\" >Latest Added Documents<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/cate