y-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Home Affairs Standing Committee Engages Justice, Constitutional and Legal Affairs Fraternity\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/home-affairs-standing-committee-engages-justice-constitutional-and-legal-affairs-fraternity\/\" title=\"Home Affairs Standing Committee Engages Justice, Constitutional and Legal Affairs Fraternity\" rel=\"bookmark\">Home Affairs Standing Committee Engages Justice, Constitutional and Legal Affairs Fraternity<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The Parliamentary Standing Committee on Home Affairs, Security, Constitutional and Legal Affairs (HASCLA) is conducting oversight engagements with selected Organizations, Ministries and Agencies (OMAs) under their ambit in Swakopmund, Erongo Region.\u00a0So far, the Committee met the Magistrates Commission to discuss staffing issues, backlog of cases and delays\u00a0 experienced in the conclusion of cases, particularly petty&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/home-affairs-standing-committee-engages-justice-constitutional-and-legal-affairs-fraternity\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Home Affairs Standing Committee Engages Justice, Constitutional and Legal Affairs Fraternity\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-13974 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Call for African leaders to prioritise fight against hunger, poverty\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/call-for-african-leaders-to-prioritise-fight-against-hunger-poverty\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/PHOTO-2023-07-19-15-38-05-1-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/PHOTO-2023-07-19-15-38-05-1-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/PHOTO-2023-07-19-15-38-05-1-780x780.jpg 780w\" alt=\"\" title=\"PHOTO-2023-07-19-15-38-05\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/call-for-african-leaders-to-prioritise-fight-against-hunger-poverty\/\" title=\"Call for African leaders to prioritise fight against hunger, poverty\" rel=\"bookmark\">Call for African leaders to prioritise fight against hunger, poverty<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/s-iikelaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Sakeus Iikela Chairperson of the National Council Hon. Lukas Sinimbo Muha, has called on African leaders to revisit their socio-economic developmental agendas and prioritise eradicating hunger and poverty on the continent. He made these remarks during a discussion on food security at the 18th Conference of Speakers and Presiding Officers in Yaound\u00e9, Cameroon. According to&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/call-for-african-leaders-to-prioritise-fight-against-hunger-poverty\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Call for African leaders to prioritise fight against hunger, poverty\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-13863 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Council Swear-in New Members\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-swear-in-new-members\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/01-scaled-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/01-scaled-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/01-scaled-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"\" title=\"01\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-swear-in-new-members\/\" title=\"National Council Swear-in New Members\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Council Swear-in New Members<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Windhoek \u2013 Landless People\u2019s Movement Constituency Councillors from the \/\/Kharas region were sworn-in as Members of Parliament in the National Council this morning, 11 July 2023. The MPs are returning Karasburg East Councillor, Hon. Anseline Vincentina Beukes and newly-elected Keetmanshoop Rural Constituency Councillor, Hon. Willem Labuschagne. The LPM seats in the National Council became vacant&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-swear-in-new-members\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Council Swear-in New Members\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-13830 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-latest-added-documents category-news category-159 category-219 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Death Notice\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/death-notice\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2