=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20720%20720&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/hambyuka-720x720.jpeg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/hambyuka-720x720.jpeg 720w\" alt=\"\" title=\"hambyuka\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/permanent-committees-of-the-pan-african-parliament-face-budget-constraints\/\" title=\"Permanent Committees of the Pan-African Parliament Face Budget Constraints\" rel=\"bookmark\">Permanent Committees of the Pan-African Parliament Face Budget Constraints<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The final week of the Second Ordinary Session of the Sixth Parliament commenced with Committee Meetings. Today, 30 May 2023, the Committee on Education, Culture, Tourism and Human Resources; Committee on Rules, Privileges and Discipline; Committee on Audit and Public Accounts as well as the Committee on Transport, Communication, Energy, Science, and Technology were the&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/permanent-committees-of-the-pan-african-parliament-face-budget-constraints\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Permanent Committees of the Pan-African Parliament Face Budget Constraints\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-13439 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Maximising the potential on mines and energy sectors in Namibia\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/it-is-necessary-to-enhance-and-strengthen-laws-deemed-inadequate-honourable-tweya\/\" title=\"Maximising the potential on mines and energy sectors in Namibia\" rel=\"bookmark\">Maximising the potential on mines and energy sectors in Namibia<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by Sakeus Kadhikwa The two Parliamentary Standing Committees of the National Assembly (Economics and Public Administration and that of Natural Resources) jointly organised a six-day oversight workshop in Swakopmund from the 29th May \u2013 03 June 2023. Which brought together a diverse group of stakeholders, including members of the Parliamentary Standing Committees on Economics&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/it-is-necessary-to-enhance-and-strengthen-laws-deemed-inadequate-honourable-tweya\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Maximising the potential on mines and energy sectors in Namibia\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-13420 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Pan-African Parliament Commemorates Africa Day, Calling for Unity and Solidarity.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/pan-african-parliament-commemorates-africa-day-calling-for-unity-and-solidarity\/\" title=\"Pan-African Parliament Commemorates Africa Day, Calling for Unity and Solidarity.\" rel=\"bookmark\">Pan-African Parliament Commemorates Africa Day, Calling for Unity and Solidarity.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Clad in beautiful and colourful traditional attire from across the continent, Members of the Pan-African Parliament (PAP) commemorated a vibrant Africa Day and 60th Anniversary of the African Union yesterday, 25 May 2023 during the Second Ordinary Session of the Sixth Parliament at its headquarters in Midrand, South Africa. The call was for a re-ignited&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/pan-african-parliament-commemorates-africa-day-calling-for-unity-and-solidarity\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Pan-African Parliament Commemorates Africa Day, Calling for Unity and Solidarity.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-13415 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Hon. Venaani Calls for Infrastructure Development to Promote Trade Across Africa\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/hon-venaani-calls-for-infrastructure-development-to-promote-trade-across-africa\/\" title=\"Hon. Venaani Calls for Infrastructure Development to Promote Trade Across Africa\" rel=\"bookmark\">Hon. Venaani Calls for Infrastructure Development to Promote Trade Across Africa<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Midrand, South Africa: The Pan-African Parliament concluded its two-day workshop on the Africa Continental Free Trade Area (AfCFTA) yesterday, 23 May 2023. The workshop which took place on the sidelines of the ongoing Second Session of the Sixth Parliament was aimed at devising strategies to accelerate continental free trade on the continent. Hon. McHenry Venaani,&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/hon-venaani-calls-for-infrastructure-development-to-promote-trade-across-africa\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Hon. Venaani Calls for Infrastructure Development to Promote Trade Across Africa\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-13407 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"African member states determined on reforming Commonwealth &#8211; Muha\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/african-member-states-determined-on-reforming-commonwealth-muha\/\" title=\"African member states determined on reforming Commonwealth &#8211; Muha\" rel=\"bookmark\">African member states determined on reforming Commonwealth &#8211; Muha<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/s-iikelaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>A MAJORITY of the African countries that are part of the Commonwealth are united behind the plan to restructure the organisation to give it relevance in the modern world. Under this plan, the member states intend to reform the organisation to address perceived imbalances and strengthen its relevance, taking into account issues such as representation,&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/african-member-states-determined-on-reforming-commonwealth-muha\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about African member states determined on reforming Commonwealth &#8211; Muha\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-13401 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-uncategorized category-159 category-39 category-1 description-off\" data-name=\"Pan-African Parliament to Define its Role in Accelerating the Implementation of AfCFTA\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/pan-african-parliament-to-define-its-role-in-accelerating-the-implementation-of-afcfta\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Pan-African_Parliament_Logo.svg_-2-768x768.png\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Pan-African_Parliament_Logo.svg_-2-768x768.png 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Pan-African_Parliament_Logo.svg_-2-800x799.png 800w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Pan-African_Parliament_Logo.svg\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/pan-african-parliament-to-define-its-role-in-accelerating-the-implementation-of-afcfta\/\" title=\"Pan-African Parliament to Define its Role in Accelerating the Implementation of AfCFTA\" rel=\"bookmark\">Pan-African Parliament to Define its Role in Accelerating the Implementation of AfCFTA<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/uncategorized\/\" >Uncategorized<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Midrand, South Africa: The Second Ordinary Session of the Sixth Pan-African Parliament (PAP) continued this morning (22 May 2023) with a workshop underscoring the theme of the African Union for the year 2023: \u201cAccelerating the African Continental Free Trade Area (AfCFTA): The Strategic Significance of the Pan-African Parliament\u201d. The aim of the seminar is to&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/pan-african-parliament-to-define-its-role-in-accelerating-the-implementation-of-afcfta\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Pan-African Parliament to Define its Role in Accelerating the Implementation of AfCFTA\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-13390 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-media-releases category-news category-159 category-76 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"China should support Africa\u2019s bid for UN Security Council seat &#8211; Muha\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/china-should-support-africas-bid-for-un-security-council-seat-muha\/\" title=\"China should support Africa\u2019s bid for UN Security Council seat &#8211; Muha\" rel=\"bookmark\">China should support Africa\u2019s bid for UN Security Council seat &#8211; Muha<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/documents\/media-releases\/\" >Media Releases<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/s-iikelaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Sakeus Iikela The Chairperson of the National Council Hon. Lukas Sinimbo Muha has called on China to use its position as a permanent member of the United Nations Security Council to advocate and support Africa\u2019s bid to secure a permanent seat on the Council. \u201cThe UN has assisted Africa in terms of getting independence and&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/china-should-support-africas-bid-for-un-security-council-seat-muha\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about China should support Africa\u2019s bid for UN Security Council seat &#8211; Muha\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-13385 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-uncategorized category-159 category-39 category-1 description-off\" data-name=\"Minister of Justice, Hon. Yvonne Dausab Delivers Keynote Speech at Parliamentary Dialogue\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/minister-of-justice-hon-yvonne-dausab-to-deliver-keynote-speech-at-parliamentary-dialogue\/\" title=\"Minister of Justice, Hon. Yvonne Dausab Delivers Keynote Speech at Parliamentary Dialogue\" rel=\"bookmark\">Minister of Justice, Hon. Yvonne Dausab Delivers Keynote Speech at Parliamentary Dialogue<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/uncategorized\/\" >Uncategorized<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The Parliamentary Dialogue with the Pan-African ParliamentCivil Society Forum is underway today, 19 May 2023, on the sidelines of the Second Session of the Sixth Pan African Parliament. The Keynote Speaker at the Parliamentary Dialogue is Namibia\u2019s Minister of Justice, Hon. Yvonne Dausab, who will look into the role of civil society in the promotion&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/minister-of-justice-hon-yvonne-dausab-to-deliver-keynote-speech-at-parliamentary-dialogue\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Minister of Justice, Hon. Yvonne Dausab Delivers Keynote Speech at Parliamentary Dialogue\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-13379 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Kenyan President Addresses Pan-African Parliament on Climate Change\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/kenyan-president-addresses-pan-african-parliament-on-climate-change\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/ruto-pan-scaled-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/ruto-pan-scaled-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/ruto-pan-scaled-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"\" title=\"ruto pan\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/kenyan-president-addresses-pan-african-parliament-on-climate-change\/\" title=\"Kenyan President Addresses Pan-African Parliament on Climate Change\" rel=\"bookmark\">Kenyan President Addresses Pan-African Parliament on Climate Change<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Kenyan President, H.E William Ruto addressed the third African Parliamentarians Summit on Climate Policy and Equity, hosted by the Pan- African Parliament today (17 May 2023) in Midrand, South Africa. President Ruto addressed the summit in his capacity as the Head of the Committee of African Heads of State and Government on Climate Change. The&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/kenyan-president-addresses-pan-african-parliament-on-climate-change\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Kenyan President Addresses Pan-African Parliament on Climate Change\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-13368 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Pan-African Parliament to Accelerate Free Trade Agreement for Africa\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/pan-african-parliament-session-aims-to-accelerate-free-trade-area-for-africa\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/3L1A9648-scaled-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/3L1A9648-scaled-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/3L1A9648-scaled-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"\" title=\"3L1A9648\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/pan-african-parliament-session-aims-to-accelerate-free-trade-area-for-africa\/\" title=\"Pan-African Parliament to Accelerate Free Trade Agreement for Africa\" rel=\"bookmark\">Pan-African Parliament to Accelerate Free Trade Agreement for Africa<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>MIDRAND, SOUTH AFRICA&#8211; The Second Ordinary Session of the Sixth Pan-African Parliament commenced on Monday, 15 May in Midrand, South Africa under the theme, \u201cAccelerating the implementation of African Continental Free Trade Area (AFCFTA). At the occasion, President of the Union of Comoros and Chairperson of the African Union, H.E Azali Assoumani delivered the Keynote&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/pan-african-parliament-session-aims-to-accelerate-free-trade-area-for-africa\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Pan-African Parliament to Accelerate Free Trade Agreement for Africa\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-13214 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Council Review Standing Committees&#8217; Activities\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-review-standing-committees-activities\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/IMG_6869-scaled-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/IMG_6869-scaled-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/IMG_6869-scaled-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_6869\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-review-standing-committees-activities\/\" title=\"National Council Review Standing Committees&#8217; Activities\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Council Review Standing Committees&#8217; Activities<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The Implementation and Coordination Committee of the National Council conducted an evaluation exercise from the 27th to the 31st of March 2023, where all Chairpersons of Standing Committees accounted for the execution of the activities of their respective Committees. The purpose of the evaluation exercise was to assess progress made on the implementation of the&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-review-standing-committees-activities\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Council Review Standing Committees&#8217; Activities\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-13187 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Parliamentary Standing Committees Map Out Activities for New Financial Year\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliamentary-standing-committees-map-out-activities-for-new-financial-year\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/annual-plan-1-scaled-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/annual-plan-1-scaled-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/annual-plan-1-scaled-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"\" title=\"annual plan 1\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliamentary-standing-committees-map-out-activities-for-new-financial-year\/\" title=\"Parliamentary Standing Committees Map Out Activities for New Financial Year\" rel=\"bookmark\">Parliamentary Standing Committees Map Out Activities for New Financial Year<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>the National Council Standing Committees\u2019 Annual Planning Session is underway at Parliament. The all-important engagement sets out key activities that Standing Committees plan to undertake in the 2023\/2024 financial year. Opening the four-day indaba, Chairperson of the National Council, Hon. Lukas Sinimbo Muha stated the importance of planning together and for Members to take full&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliamentary-standing-committees-map-out-activities-for-new-financial-year\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Parliamentary Standing Committees Map Out Activities for New Financial Year\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-12928 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Council Signs Cooperation Agreement with Federal Council of the Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-signs-cooperation-agreement-with-federal-council-of-the-federal-assembly-of-the-russian-federation\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20683%20683&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/russia-683x683.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/russia-683x683.jpg 683w\" alt=\"\" title=\"russia\" width=\"683\" height=\"683\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-signs-cooperation-agreement-with-federal-council-of-the-federal-assembly-of-the-russian-federation\/\" title=\"National Council Signs Cooperation Agreement with Federal Council of the Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Council Signs Cooperation Agreement with Federal Council of the Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>On the 22nd of March, the Chairperson of the National Council, Hon. Sinimbo Lukas Muha entered into a historic cooperation agreement with the Federal Council of the Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation, in Moscow, Russia. The signing of the cooperation agreement stems from Her Excellency, Mrs. Valentina Matviyenko, Chairperson of the Federal Council of&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-signs-cooperation-agreement-with-federal-council-of-the-federal-assembly-of-the-russian-federation\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Council Signs Cooperation Agreement with Federal Council of the Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-12849 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Namibia and Russia sign Parliamentary cooperation agreement\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibia-and-russia-sign-parliamentary-cooperation-agreement\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/212A3407-scaled-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/212A3407-scaled-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/212A3407-scaled-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"\" title=\"212A3407\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibia-and-russia-sign-parliamentary-cooperation-agreement\/\" title=\"Namibia and Russia sign Parliamentary cooperation agreement\" rel=\"bookmark\">Namibia and Russia sign Parliamentary cooperation agreement<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/s-iikelaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>By: Sakeus Iikela Namibia\u2019s National Council and the Federal Council of the Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation on Wednesday signed an agreement which will facilitate the interaction and cooperation between Members of Parliament and staff of the two countries. The Chairperson of the National Council Hon, Lukas Sinimbo Muha, who is in Russia for&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibia-and-russia-sign-parliamentary-cooperation-agreement\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Namibia and Russia sign Parliamentary cooperation agreement\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-12830 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-latest-added-documents category-media-releases-2023 category-news category-219 category-251 category-39 description-off\" d