><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Venezuelan Member of the Latin-American and Caribbean Parliament, known as the Parlatino, Mr. Jullo Rafael Chavez Melendez paid a courtesy call on the National Council Chairperson. In their brief discussion, Hon. Lukas Muha expressed gratitude to Venezuela and its people for their contribution to Namibia\u2019s independence, as well as the good relations the two countries&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/venezuelan-member-of-the-latin-american-and-caribbean-parliament-pays-courtesy-call-on-chairperson\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Venezuelan Member of the Latin-American and Caribbean Parliament Pays Courtesy Call on Chairperson\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-12087 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"REGIONAL OVERSIGHT VISITS BY THE STANDING COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION, SCIENCE, ICT AND YOUTH DEVELOPMENT UNCOVER CHALLENGES IN COMMUNITY HOSTELS ACROSS THE COUNTRY\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/regional-oversight-visits-by-the-standing-committee-on-education-science-ict-and-youth-development-uncover-challenges-in-community-hostels-across-the-country\/\" title=\"REGIONAL OVERSIGHT VISITS BY THE STANDING COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION, SCIENCE, ICT AND YOUTH DEVELOPMENT UNCOVER CHALLENGES IN COMMUNITY HOSTELS ACROSS THE COUNTRY\" rel=\"bookmark\">REGIONAL OVERSIGHT VISITS BY THE STANDING COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION, SCIENCE, ICT AND YOUTH DEVELOPMENT UNCOVER CHALLENGES IN COMMUNITY HOSTELS ACROSS THE COUNTRY<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The Parliamentary Standing Committee on Education, Science, ICT and Youth Development is undertaking regional visits to selected schools in the Kunene, Omusati, Kavango West, Kavango East, Zambezi, Erongo, Otjozondjupa, Omaheke, \/\/Kharas, Hardap and Khomas regions to assess the status of community hostels. The oversight activity, which commenced on the 29th of August will conclude on&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/regional-oversight-visits-by-the-standing-committee-on-education-science-ict-and-youth-development-uncover-challenges-in-community-hostels-across-the-country\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about REGIONAL OVERSIGHT VISITS BY THE STANDING COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION, SCIENCE, ICT AND YOUTH DEVELOPMENT UNCOVER CHALLENGES IN COMMUNITY HOSTELS ACROSS THE COUNTRY\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-12078 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker recall last moment with late wife in moving tribute\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-recall-last-moment-with-late-wife-in-moving-tribute\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/01-scaled-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/01-scaled-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/01-scaled-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"\"  width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-recall-last-moment-with-late-wife-in-moving-tribute\/\" title=\"Speaker recall last moment with late wife in moving tribute\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker recall last moment with late wife in moving tribute<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/sanzila\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; Speaker of the National Assembly Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi recalled his last moments with his late wife, in a moving tribute he delivered during a memorial service that was held on Thursday (18\/08\/22) to honour her memory. Jane Katjavivi lost her life in the presence of her husband while&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-recall-last-moment-with-late-wife-in-moving-tribute\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker recall last moment with late wife in moving tribute\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-12060 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"MPS meet Government Ministries to Gain Wider Understanding on Bills Under Review\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/mps-meet-government-ministries-to-gain-wider-understanding-on-bills-under-review\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/nc_event-e1660226064730-600x600.jpeg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/nc_event-e1660226064730-600x600.jpeg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"nc_event\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/mps-meet-government-ministries-to-gain-wider-understanding-on-bills-under-review\/\" title=\"MPS meet Government Ministries to Gain Wider Understanding on Bills Under Review\" rel=\"bookmark\">MPS meet Government Ministries to Gain Wider Understanding on Bills Under Review<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Various representatives from Government Ministries held briefing sessions with Members of Parliament today, 9 August 2022. The meetings were for MPs to be sensitized and given the gist of the proposed amendments to Bills that were referred from the National Assembly to the National Council for review. First up, was the Ministry of Industrialization and&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/mps-meet-government-ministries-to-gain-wider-understanding-on-bills-under-review\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about MPS meet Government Ministries to Gain Wider Understanding on Bills Under Review\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-12056 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-latest-added-documents category-media-releases-2022 category-news category-159 category-219 category-224 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"MESSAGE OF CONDOLENCES ON THE PASSING OF MADAME JANE ROSEMARY KATJAVIVI; 09 AUGUST 2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/message-of-condolences-on-the-passing-of-madame-jane-rosemary-katjavivi-09-august-2022\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/media_logo-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/media_logo-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"media_logo\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/message-of-condolences-on-the-passing-of-madame-jane-rosemary-katjavivi-09-august-2022\/\" title=\"MESSAGE OF CONDOLENCES ON THE PASSING OF MADAME JANE ROSEMARY KATJAVIVI; 09 AUGUST 2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">MESSAGE OF CONDOLENCES ON THE PASSING OF MADAME JANE ROSEMARY KATJAVIVI; 09 AUGUST 2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/latest-added-documents\/\" >Latest Added Documents<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/documents\/media-releases\/media-releases-2022\/\" >Media Releases - 2022<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The National Assembly hereby informs the Namibian people of the passing on of Madame Rosemary Jane Katjavivi, the Spouse of the Speaker of the National Assembly. MESSAGE OF CONDOLENCES ON THE PASSING OF MRS JANE KATJAVIVI<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/message-of-condolences-on-the-passing-of-madame-jane-rosemary-katjavivi-09-august-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about MESSAGE OF CONDOLENCES ON THE PASSING OF MADAME JANE ROSEMARY KATJAVIVI; 09 AUGUST 2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-12051 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"MPs of National Council Frustrated with Progress Made on CDF Bill\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/mps-of-national-council-frustrated-with-progress-made-on-cdf-bill\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20538%20538&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/nc_cdf1-538x538.jpeg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/nc_cdf1-538x538.jpeg 538w\" alt=\"\" title=\"nc_cdf1\" width=\"538\" height=\"538\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/mps-of-national-council-frustrated-with-progress-made-on-cdf-bill\/\" title=\"MPs of National Council Frustrated with Progress Made on CDF Bill\" rel=\"bookmark\">MPs of National Council Frustrated with Progress Made on CDF Bill<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The Ministry of Urban and Rural Development briefed Members of Parliament on the long-awaited Constituency Development Fund on Friday, 5 August 2022. MPs expressed disappointment at the slow pace and lack of urgency with which the Bill, commonly referred to as the CDF Bill, has been handled. MPs stressed that the passing and implementation of&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/mps-of-national-council-frustrated-with-progress-made-on-cdf-bill\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about MPs of National Council Frustrated with Progress Made on CDF Bill\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-12004 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Deputy Speaker happy with GBV victim friendly court\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/deputy-speaker-happy-with-gbv-victim-friendly-court\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/07\/GBV-scaled-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/07\/GBV-scaled-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/07\/GBV-scaled-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"Deputy Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Loide Kasingo (middle) with Members of Parliament and other participants shortly after the official opening of the workshop\" title=\"Deputy Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Loide Kasingo (middle) with Members of Parliament and other participants shortly after the official opening of the workshop\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/deputy-speaker-happy-with-gbv-victim-friendly-court\/\" title=\"Deputy Speaker happy with GBV victim friendly court\" rel=\"bookmark\">Deputy Speaker happy with GBV victim friendly court<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/sanzila\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Swakopmund &#8211; Deputy Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Loide Kasingo has commended the Ministry of Justice for inaugurating a GBV victim friendly court noting that such a gesture would go a long way in strengthening the implementation of the existing legal frameworks aimed at eradicating gender-based violence. Deputy Speaker Kasingo&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/deputy-speaker-happy-with-gbv-victim-friendly-court\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Deputy Speaker happy with GBV victim friendly court\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-11960 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Namibian MPs call for collaboration to avert energy crisis in SADC, 11\/07\/2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibian-mps-call-for-collaboration-to-avert-energy-crisis-in-sadc-11-07-2022\/\" title=\"Namibian MPs call for collaboration to avert energy crisis in SADC, 11\/07\/2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">Namibian MPs call for collaboration to avert energy crisis in SADC, 11\/07\/2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Lilongwe, Malawi &#8211; SADC countries should collaborate and exploit potential energy sources existing in the region in order to curtail the long-standing energy crisis that has been exacerbated by the effects of the ongoing war in eastern Europe. These sentiments were shared by Hon. Agnes Kafula at a symposium of the&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/namibian-mps-call-for-collaboration-to-avert-energy-crisis-in-sadc-11-07-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Namibian MPs call for collaboration to avert energy crisis in SADC, 11\/07\/2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-11903 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Council Chairperson Lauds Election of New PAP President\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-chairperson-lauds-election-of-new-pap-president\/\" title=\"National Council Chairperson Lauds Election of New PAP President\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Council Chairperson Lauds Election of New PAP President<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Zimbabwean Chief, Fortune Charumbira was elected as the new President of the Pan-African Parliament (PAP) late Wednesday evening (29 June 2022). Charumbira\u2019s election was widely celebrated in Southern Africa as he is first person from the sub-region to lead PAP. Although he was the sole presidential candidate, running for PAP presidency requires the support of&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-chairperson-lauds-election-of-new-pap-president\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Council Chairperson Lauds Election of New PAP President\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11787 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"MESSAGE OF CONDOLENCES BY HON. LUKAS SINIMBO MUHA, CHAIRPERSON OF THE NATIONAL COUNCIL, ON THE PASSING OF FORMER NATIONAL COUNCIL MEMBER OF PARLIAMENT, THE LATE HON. AMBROSIUS KANDJII.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/message-of-condolences-by-hon-lukas-sinimbo-muha-chairperson-of-the-national-council-on-the-passing-of-former-national-council-member-of-parliament-the-late-hon-ambrosius-kandjii\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/kandji_copy-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/kandji_copy-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"kandji_copy\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/message-of-condolences-by-hon-lukas-sinimbo-muha-chairperson-of-the-national-council-on-the-passing-of-former-national-council-member-of-parliament-the-late-hon-ambrosius-kandjii\/\" title=\"MESSAGE OF CONDOLENCES BY HON. LUKAS SINIMBO MUHA, CHAIRPERSON OF THE NATIONAL COUNCIL, ON THE PASSING OF FORMER NATIONAL COUNCIL MEMBER OF PARLIAMENT, THE LATE HON. AMBROSIUS KANDJII.\" rel=\"bookmark\">MESSAGE OF CONDOLENCES BY HON. LUKAS SINIMBO MUHA, CHAIRPERSON OF THE NATIONAL COUNCIL, ON THE PASSING OF FORMER NATIONAL COUNCIL MEMBER OF PARLIAMENT, THE LATE HON. AMBROSIUS KANDJII.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>With deep sadness I, Lukas Sinimbo Muha, Chairperson of the National Council, have learned of the passing of my comrade, friend and former National Council Member, late Comrade Ambrosius Kandjii, who passed away in the early hours of Wednesday, 8 June 2022 in Gobabis. Late Comrade Kandjii was a Member of the National Council, Parliament&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/message-of-condolences-by-hon-lukas-sinimbo-muha-chairperson-of-the-national-council-on-the-passing-of-former-national-council-member-of-parliament-the-late-hon-ambrosius-kandjii\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about MESSAGE OF CONDOLENCES BY HON. LUKAS SINIMBO MUHA, CHAIRPERSON OF THE NATIONAL COUNCIL, ON THE PASSING OF FORMER NATIONAL COUNCIL MEMBER OF PARLIAMENT, THE LATE HON. AMBROSIUS KANDJII.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11776 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Late National Council Staff Member Remembered as a Remarkable Person at Memorial Service Held in His Honour\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/late-national-council-staff-member-remembered-as-a-remarkable-person-at-memorial-service-held-in-his-honour\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/pro-memorial-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/pro-memorial-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/pro-memorial-809x809.jpg 809w\" alt=\"\" title=\"pro memorial\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/late-national-council-staff-member-remembered-as-a-remarkable-person-at-memorial-service-held-in-his-honour\/\" title=\"Late National Council Staff Member Remembered as a Remarkable Person at Memorial Service Held in His Honour\" rel=\"bookmark\">Late National Council Staff Member Remembered as a Remarkable Person at Memorial Service Held in His Honour<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Family, friends and colleagues of the late Protasius Nambudhi descended upon the Corpus Christ Roman Catholic Church in Windhoek yesterday, 8 June 2022 to pay their respects to the late Nambudhi, who passed away on Friday, 3 June 2022 in a tragic car accident. Speaking on behalf of the National Council, the Administrative Head, Adv.&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/late-national-council-staff-member-remembered-as-a-remarkable-person-at-memorial-service-held-in-his-honour\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Late National Council Staff Member Remembered as a Remarkable Person at Memorial Service Held in His Honour\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11767 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Council Staff Pay a Visit to the Family of Late Colleague\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-staff-pay-a-visit-to-the-family-of-late-colleague\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/pro-family-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/pro-family-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/pro-family-867x867.jpg 867w\" alt=\"\" title=\"pro family\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-staff-pay-a-visit-to-the-family-of-late-colleague\/\" title=\"National Council Staff Pay a Visit to the Family of Late Colleague\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Council Staff Pay a Visit to the Family of Late Colleague<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Management and staff of the National Council paid a visit to the family of the late Protasius Nambudhi who passed away on Friday, 3 June 2022. Speaking on behalf of the grieving staff members at the family home, Director for General Services, Research and Information, Ms. Hilia Amakali thanked the family of the late for&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-staff-pay-a-visit-to-the-family-of-late-colleague\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Council Staff Pay a Visit to the Family of Late Colleague\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11745 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Death Notice of Mr. Protasius Nambudhi, National Council Staff Member\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/death-notice-of-mr-protasius-nambudhi-national-council-staff-member\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/late_prota-copy-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/late_prota-copy-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"late_prota copy\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/death-notice-of-mr-protasius-nambudhi-national-council-staff-member\/\" title=\"Death Notice of Mr. Protasius Nambudhi, National Council Staff Member\" rel=\"bookmark\">Death Notice of Mr. Protasius Nambudhi, National Council Staff Member<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>With deep sadness, the Secretary to the National Council, Adv. Tousy Namiseb, hereby, announces the untimely passing of Mr. Protasius Nambudhi, who was a Security Operations Officer in the Security and Operations Division: Office of the Secretary. Mr. Nambudhi passed away on Friday, 3 June 2022 in a tragic car accident. Mr. Nambudhi, or Prota&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/death-notice-of-mr-protasius-nambudhi-national-council-staff-member\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Death Notice of Mr. Protasius Nambudhi, National Council Staff Member\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11730 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Parliamentarians and ReconNamibia Representatives Discuss Oil and Gas Exploration in the Kavango Regions\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/reconnamibia-mps-discuss-oil-and-gas-exploration-in-the-kavango-regions\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/recon-meet-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/recon-meet-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/recon-meet-810x810.jpg 810w\" alt=\"\" title=\"recon meet\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/reconnamibia-mps-discuss-oil-and-gas-exploration-in-the-kavango-regions\/\" title=\"Parliamentarians and ReconNamibia Representatives Discuss Oil and Gas Exploration in the Kavango Regions\" rel=\"bookmark\">Parliamentarians and ReconNamibia Representatives Discuss Oil and Gas Exploration in the Kavango Regions<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>ReconNamibia, a subsidiary of the Canadian-based oil and gas company,\u00a0ReconAfrica held a briefing session yesterday (30 May 2022) with Members of Parliament to expound on their oil and gas exploration expedition in the Kavango regions. The purpose of the meeting was to an information sharing briefing on the status of oil discovery in Namibia as&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/reconnamibia-mps-discuss-oil-and-gas-exploration-in-the-kavango-regions\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Parliamentarians and ReconNamibia Representatives Discuss Oil and Gas Exploration in the Kavango Regions\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11725 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Parliamentarians and Experts Engage on Tackling Climate Change\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliamentarians-and-experts-engage-on-tackling-climate-change\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/forest-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/forest-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/forest-809x809.jpg 809w\" alt=\"\" title=\"forest\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliamentarians-and-experts-engage-on-tackling-climate-change\/\" title=\"Parliamentarians and Experts Engage on Tackling Climate Change\" rel=\"bookmark\">Parliamentarians and Experts Engage on Tackling Climate Change<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Members of Parliament attended a Parliamentary Public Engagement on Tackling Climate Change \u2013 Forestry as a Key Sector today, 20 May 2022. The aim of the engagement is to strengthen the Namibian Governments\u2019 work in addressing the unsustainable use of timber resources and uncontrolled deforestation.\u00a0Officially opening the event, Chairperson of the National Council, Hon. Lukas&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliamentarians-and-experts-engage-on-tackling-climate-change\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Parliamentarians and Experts Engage on Tackling Climate Change\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11707 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Hon Nekongo sworn in as MP in National Assembly, 12\/05\/2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/hon-nekongo-sworn-in-as-mp-in-national-assembly-12-05-2022\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Ephraim-2-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Ephraim-2-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Ephraim 2\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/hon-nekongo-sworn-in-as-mp-in-national-assembly-12-05-2022\/\" title=\"Hon Nekongo sworn in as MP in National Assembly, 12\/05\/2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">Hon Nekongo sworn in as MP in National Assembly, 12\/05\/2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Hon. Ephraim Nekongo was today (12\/05\/2022) sworn in as a Member of Parliament in the National Assembly by the Chief Justice, His Honour Peter Shivute. His appointment follows the resignation of Hon. Leon Jooste from the National Assembly.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/hon-nekongo-sworn-in-as-mp-in-national-assembly-12-05-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Hon Nekongo sworn in as MP in National Assembly, 12\/05\/2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11686 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"South African Provincial MPs pay courtesy call on Speaker, 10\/05\/2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/south-african-provincial-mps-pay-courtesy-call-on-speaker-10-05-2022\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/SA-2-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/SA-2-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"SA 2\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/south-african-provincial-mps-pay-courtesy-call-on-speaker-10-05-2022\/\" title=\"South African Provincial MPs pay courtesy call on Speaker, 10\/05\/2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">South African Provincial MPs pay courtesy call on Speaker, 10\/05\/2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; Members of Parliament from the South African National Council of Provinces (NCOP) that are visiting the National Council for benchmarking, paid a courtesy call on the Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi today (10\/05\/2022). The NCOP is the equivalent of the National Council in Namibia.&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/south-african-provincial-mps-pay-courtesy-call-on-speaker-10-05-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about South African Provincial MPs pay courtesy call on Speaker, 10\/05\/2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11685 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Visiting NCOP Members Pay Courtesy Call on Chairperson\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/visiting-ncop-members-pay-courtesy-call-on-chairperson\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/ncop-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/ncop-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/ncop-810x810.jpg 810w\" alt=\"\" title=\"ncop\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/visiting-ncop-members-pay-courtesy-call-on-chairperson\/\" title=\"Visiting NCOP Members Pay Courtesy Call on Chairperson\" rel=\"bookmark\">Visiting NCOP Members Pay Courtesy Call on Chairperson<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Members of the South African Parliament in the National Council of Provinces (NCOP), paid a courtesy call on the Chairperson of the National Council, Hon. Lukas Muha earlier today, 10 May 2022. The Chairperson welcomed the visiting delegation heartily, noting that due to its representative role, a visit to the National Council equates a visit&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/visiting-ncop-members-pay-courtesy-call-on-chairperson\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Visiting NCOP Members Pay Courtesy Call on Chairperson\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11681 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Parliamentarian Practice and Conduct Course for Members of Parliament Officially Launched\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliamentarian-practice-and-conduct-course-for-members-of-parliament-officially-launched\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/unam-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/unam-768x768.jpg 768w\" alt=\"\" title=\"unam\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliamentarian-practice-and-conduct-course-for-members-of-parliament-officially-launched\/\" title=\"Parliamentarian Practice and Conduct Course for Members of Parliament Officially Launched\" rel=\"bookmark\">Parliamentarian Practice and Conduct Course for Members of Parliament Officially Launched<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The official launch of the Parliamentarian Practice and Conduct Course of Members of Parliament in the National Council took place yesterday, 9 May 2022 at Parliament. Speaking at the event, the Chairperson of the National Council Hon. Lukas Muha stated that a program of this nature enhances the general understanding of the separation of powers&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliamentarian-practice-and-conduct-course-for-members-of-parliament-officially-launched\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Parliamentarian Practice and Conduct Course for Members of Parliament Officially Launched\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11630 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Palestine&#8217;s Ambassador meets the Speaker, 21\/04\/2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/palestines-ambassador-meets-the-speaker-21-04-2022\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/palestine-2-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/palestine-2-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\"  width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/palestines-ambassador-meets-the-speaker-21-04-2022\/\" title=\"Palestine&#8217;s Ambassador meets the Speaker, 21\/04\/2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">Palestine&#8217;s Ambassador meets the Speaker, 21\/04\/2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The Ambassador of the State of Palestine to Namibia, H.E. Hanan Jarrar paid a Courtesy call on the Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi today (21\/04\/2022). The two exchanged views on the need for Parliamentary cooperation between Namibia and Palestine. Their discussion embedded on various areas of collaboration aimed at reinforcing the&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/palestines-ambassador-meets-the-speaker-21-04-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Palestine&#8217;s Ambassador meets the Speaker, 21\/04\/2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11612 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Standing Committee on Home Affairs, Security, Constitutional and Legal Affairs Assess Border Posts and Civil Registrations\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/standing-committee-on-home-affairs-security-constitutional-and-legal-affairs-assesses-border-posts-and-civil-registrations\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/HACSLA-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/HACSLA-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/HACSLA-810x810.jpg 810w\" alt=\"\" title=\"HACSLA\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/standing-committee-on-home-affairs-security-constitutional-and-legal-affairs-assesses-border-posts-and-civil-registrations\/\" title=\"Standing Committee on Home Affairs, Security, Constitutional and Legal Affairs Assess Border Posts and Civil Registrations\" rel=\"bookmark\">Standing Committee on Home Affairs, Security, Constitutional and Legal Affairs Assess Border Posts and Civil Registrations<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The National Council Standing Committee on Home Affairs, Security, Constitutional and Legal Affairs (HASCLA) conducted oversight visits to several national border posts across the country to assess the status of the borders from the 7th\u00a0to the 25th\u00a0of March 2022. The oversight activity was two-fold, as while on the visit to gazetted border posts, the Standing&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/standing-committee-on-home-affairs-security-constitutional-and-legal-affairs-assesses-border-posts-and-civil-registrations\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Standing Committee on Home Affairs, Security, Constitutional and Legal Affairs Assess Border Posts and Civil Registrations\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11561 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker engages ECN leadership, 11\/04\/2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-engages-ecn-leadership-11-04-2022\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ECN1-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ECN1-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"ECN1\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-engages-ecn-leadership-11-04-2022\/\" title=\"Speaker engages ECN leadership, 11\/04\/2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker engages ECN leadership, 11\/04\/2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The Speaker of the National Assembly Hon Prof Peter Katjavivi today (11\/04\/2022) held a meeting with the Electoral Commission of Namibia (ECN) on issues of mutual interest. The meeting also served as a platform to introduce new ECN Commissioners. The Chairperson of the ECN Elsie Nghikembua and the Chief Electoral Officer Theo Mujoro led the&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-engages-ecn-leadership-11-04-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker engages ECN leadership, 11\/04\/2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11555 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Japan Ambassador bids farewell to Speaker, 08\/04\/2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/japan-ambassador-bids-farewell-to-speaker-08-04-2022\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/japn-2-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/japn-2-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"japn 2\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/japan-ambassador-bids-farewell-to-speaker-08-04-2022\/\" title=\"Japan Ambassador bids farewell to Speaker, 08\/04\/2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">Japan Ambassador bids farewell to Speaker, 08\/04\/2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; Japan Ambassador to Namibia, H.E. Hideaki Harada bid farewell to the Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi today (08\/04\/22). H.E. Harada\u2019s term of office as Ambassador in Namibia started in 2018. Ambassador Harada noted during the farewell that Japan\u2019s interest has always been to strengthen political,&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/japan-ambassador-bids-farewell-to-speaker-08-04-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Japan Ambassador bids farewell to Speaker, 08\/04\/2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11527 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Committee on Constitutional and Legal Affairs engages MEFT on Bwabwata, 31 March 2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/committee-on-constitutional-and-legal-affairs-engages-meft-on-bwabwata-31-march-2022\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MEFT-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MEFT-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"MEFT\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/committee-on-constitutional-and-legal-affairs-engages-meft-on-bwabwata-31-march-2022\/\" title=\"Committee on Constitutional and Legal Affairs engages MEFT on Bwabwata, 31 March 2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">Committee on Constitutional and Legal Affairs engages MEFT on Bwabwata, 31 March 2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; The Ministry of Environment, Forestry and Tourism says that government held several consultations with different stakeholders including the Chief of the Hambukushu Traditional Authority, Fumu Erwin Mbambo regarding the issue of Bwabwata National Park. The Ministry says that according to the Cabinet submission of 08 June 1999, the Ministry of Lands, Resettlement and Rehabilitation,&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/committee-on-constitutional-and-legal-affairs-engages-meft-on-bwabwata-31-march-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Committee on Constitutional and Legal Affairs engages MEFT on Bwabwata, 31 March 2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11479 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker pleads for close collaboration to fight climate change, 23\/03\/3022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-pleads-for-close-collaboration-to-fight-climate-change-23-03-3022\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Untitled-1-4-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Untitled-1-4-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Untitled-1\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-pleads-for-close-collaboration-to-fight-climate-change-23-03-3022\/\" title=\"Speaker pleads for close collaboration to fight climate change, 23\/03\/3022\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker pleads for close collaboration to fight climate change, 23\/03\/3022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi says even though Namibia\u2019s contribution to greenhouse gas emissions is negligible, it continues to bear the brunt of climate change. Hon. Katjavivi mentioned this recently during a debate at the ongoing Inter Parliamentary Union (IPU) 144th Assembly taking place in&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-pleads-for-close-collaboration-to-fight-climate-change-23-03-3022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker pleads for close collaboration to fight climate change, 23\/03\/3022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11474 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Constitutional and Legal Affairs Committee meets the Hambukushu,  Khwe communities\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/constitutional-and-legal-affairs-committee-meets-the-hambukushu-khwe-communities\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Untitled-1-3-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Untitled-1-3-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Untitled-1\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/constitutional-and-legal-affairs-committee-meets-the-hambukushu-khwe-communities\/\" title=\"Constitutional and Legal Affairs Committee meets the Hambukushu,  Khwe communities\" rel=\"bookmark\">Constitutional and Legal Affairs Committee meets the Hambukushu,  Khwe communities<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>BWABWATA-The Parliamentary Standing Committee on Constitutional and Legal Affairs undertook a Fact-Finding visit to Bwabwata National Park from 14 March 2022 to 17 March 2022 prompted by a petition submitted to the National Assembly on 19 November 2021 by the Hambukushu Traditional Authority. The petition titled \u201cPetition on the Management of Bwabwata Communal Land by&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/constitutional-and-legal-affairs-committee-meets-the-hambukushu-khwe-communities\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Constitutional and Legal Affairs Committee meets the Hambukushu,  Khwe communities\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11432 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Chairperson&#8217;s Outreach Enhances Public Participation in the Legislative Process\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/chairpersons-outreach-enhances-public-participation-in-the-legislative-process\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/outreach-scaled-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/outreach-scaled-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/outreach-scaled-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"\" title=\"outreach\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/chairpersons-outreach-enhances-public-participation-in-the-legislative-process\/\" title=\"Chairperson&#8217;s Outreach Enhances Public Participation in the Legislative Process\" rel=\"bookmark\">Chairperson&#8217;s Outreach Enhances Public Participation in the Legislative Process<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Chairperson of the National Council, Hon. Lukas Sinimbo Muha&#8217;s outreach programme continued on the 21st of February 2022, with the Presiding Officer paying a Courtesy visit to the Governor of the Kavango East region, Hon. Bonifatius Wakudumo were various developmental and socio-economic issues in the region were discussed. This was followed by a well-attended community&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/chairpersons-outreach-enhances-public-participation-in-the-legislative-process\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Chairperson&#8217;s Outreach Enhances Public Participation in the Legislative Process\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11424 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Council Marks 29 Years as a House of the Namibian Parliament\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-marks-29-years-as-a-house-of-the-namibian-parliament\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Hon.-Lukas-Sinimbo-Muha-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Hon.-Lukas-Sinimbo-Muha-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Hon.-Lukas-Sinimbo-Muha-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Hon. Lukas Sinimbo Muha\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-marks-29-years-as-a-house-of-the-namibian-parliament\/\" title=\"National Council Marks 29 Years as a House of the Namibian Parliament\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Council Marks 29 Years as a House of the Namibian Parliament<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>On 23 February 2022, the National Council celebrated 29 years. The National Council held its inaugural sitting on 23 February 1993, after the first Regional and Local Authority Elections held in November 1992 elected the first Regional Councillors in an independent Namibia. At inception, the National Council had only two parties represented in the House&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-marks-29-years-as-a-house-of-the-namibian-parliament\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Council Marks 29 Years as a House of the Namibian Parliament\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11406 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-media-releases-2022 category-news category-224 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"NATIONAL COUNCIL SECRETARIAT CONSULTATIVE MEETING WITH CHIEF REGIONAL OFFICERS: 15 MARCH 2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-secretariat-consultative-meeting-with-chief-regional-officers-15-march-2022\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20109%20109&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/logo-109x109.png\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/logo-109x109.png 109w\" alt=\"\" title=\"logo\" width=\"109\" height=\"109\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-secretariat-consultative-meeting-with-chief-regional-officers-15-march-2022\/\" title=\"NATIONAL COUNCIL SECRETARIAT CONSULTATIVE MEETING WITH CHIEF REGIONAL OFFICERS: 15 MARCH 2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">NATIONAL COUNCIL SECRETARIAT CONSULTATIVE MEETING WITH CHIEF REGIONAL OFFICERS: 15 MARCH 2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/documents\/media-releases\/media-releases-2022\/\" >Media Releases - 2022<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The National Council wishes to invite members of the media to cover the opening session of the consultative meeting between the National Council\u2019s Secretariat and Chief Regional Officers representing all 14 regions in the country. The objective of the meeting is to strengthen cooperation between the National Council Secretariat and various regional councils to improve&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-secretariat-consultative-meeting-with-chief-regional-officers-15-march-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about NATIONAL COUNCIL SECRETARIAT CONSULTATIVE MEETING WITH CHIEF REGIONAL OFFICERS: 15 MARCH 2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11318 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-latest-added-documents category-news category-219 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Sitting Adjustment\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sitting-adjustment\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%2039%2039&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/logo-small-e1646318734884-39x39.png\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/logo-small-e1646318734884-39x39.png 39w\" alt=\"\" title=\"logo small\" width=\"39\" height=\"39\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sitting-adjustment\/\" title=\"Sitting Adjustment\" rel=\"bookmark\">Sitting Adjustment<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/latest-added-documents\/\" >Latest Added Documents<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The sitting of Monday, 7 March 2022 has been cancelled. However, the Assembly will sit on Tuesday, 8 March 2022 onwardSitting Adjustment<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sitting-adjustment\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Sitting Adjustment\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-11266 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"SADCOPAC Office Bearers meet the Speaker, 22\/02\/2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sadcopac-office-bearers-meet-the-speaker-22-02-2022\/\" title=\"SADCOPAC Office Bearers meet the Speaker, 22\/02\/2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">SADCOPAC Office Bearers meet the Speaker, 22\/02\/2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>WINDHOEK- Office Bearers and Secretariat from the Southern Africa Development Community Organisation of Public Accounts Committees (SDACOPAC) today (22\/02\/2022) met with the Speaker of the National Assembly Hon Prof Peter Katjavivi as they continue with their three-day working visit to the parliament of Namibia. The Speaker has informed the SDACOPAC delegation that the National Assembly&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sadcopac-office-bearers-meet-the-speaker-22-02-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about SADCOPAC Office Bearers meet the Speaker, 22\/02\/2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11263 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"SADCOPAC enters into MoU with SADCPF , 21\/02\/2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sadcopac-enters-into-mou-with-sadcpf-21-02-2022\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/24_ed-1-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/24_ed-1-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"24_ed\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sadcopac-enters-into-mou-with-sadcpf-21-02-2022\/\" title=\"SADCOPAC enters into MoU with SADCPF , 21\/02\/2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">SADCOPAC enters into MoU with SADCPF , 21\/02\/2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; The Southern Africa Development Community Organisation of Public Accounts Committees (SADCOPAC) has signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) with the SADC Parliamentary Forum (SADC PF) to empower Members of Parliament (MPs) from the member states to effectively carry out their functions of oversight over public sector finances as well as promoting good governance in&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sadcopac-enters-into-mou-with-sadcpf-21-02-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about SADCOPAC enters into MoU with SADCPF , 21\/02\/2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11242 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"SADCOPAC Office Bearers visit Namibia, 21\/02\/2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sadcopac-office-bearers-visit-namibia-21-02-2022\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/1_ed1-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/1_ed1-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"1_ed1\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sadcopac-office-bearers-visit-namibia-21-02-2022\/\" title=\"SADCOPAC Office Bearers visit Namibia, 21\/02\/2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">SADCOPAC Office Bearers visit Namibia, 21\/02\/2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; Windhoek- Office Bearers from the Southern Africa Development Community Organisation of Public Accounts Committees (SADCOPAC) and Secretariat are here in Namibia for a three-day (21-23 February 2022) working visit to the Parliament of Namibia. The aim of the visit is to discuss the role and objectives of SADCOPAC and the progress on the implementation&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/sadcopac-office-bearers-visit-namibia-21-02-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about SADCOPAC Office Bearers visit Namibia, 21\/02\/2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11226 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Week One of the Chairperson\u2019s Outreach Programme Successfully Concluded\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/week-one-of-the-chairpersons-outreach-programme-successfully-concluded\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Outreach-Otjiwarongo-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Outreach-Otjiwarongo-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Outreach-Otjiwarongo-960x960.jpg 960w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Outreach Otjiwarongo\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/week-one-of-the-chairpersons-outreach-programme-successfully-concluded\/\" title=\"Week One of the Chairperson\u2019s Outreach Programme Successfully Concluded\" rel=\"bookmark\">Week One of the Chairperson\u2019s Outreach Programme Successfully Concluded<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>First in kick-starting the events of the two-week long activities which started on Monday, 14 February, was a courtesy call on the Governor of the Otjozondjupa Region, Hon. James Uerikua, where the National Council Chairperson, Hon. Lukas Muha shared the purpose and aim of the regional visits. After the courtesy call on the Governor, the&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/week-one-of-the-chairpersons-outreach-programme-successfully-concluded\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Week One of the Chairperson\u2019s Outreach Programme Successfully Concluded\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-11124 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Council Staff Meet to Formulate a New Five-Year Strategic Plan\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-staff-meet-to-formulate-a-new-five-year-strategic-plan\/\" title=\"National Council Staff Meet to Formulate a New Five-Year Strategic Plan\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Council Staff Meet to Formulate a New Five-Year Strategic Plan<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Pamela Mate Senior Staff of the National Council together with Members of the Ministerial Implementation Team (MIT), are meeting to formulate and craft a new Strategic Plan for the 2022 \u2013 2027 period. Prior to the pre-working workshop meeting currently underway, the respective Directorates within the institution had one-on-one sessions with the consultant, in which&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-staff-meet-to-formulate-a-new-five-year-strategic-plan\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Council Staff Meet to Formulate a New Five-Year Strategic Plan\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11122 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Chairperson to Embark on Outreach Visits to the Regions\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/chairperson-to-embark-on-outreach-visits-to-the-regions\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20136%20136&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/l_muha-136x136.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/l_muha-136x136.jpg 136w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Hon. Lukas Sinimbo Muha\" width=\"136\" height=\"136\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/chairperson-to-embark-on-outreach-visits-to-the-regions\/\" title=\"Chairperson to Embark on Outreach Visits to the Regions\" rel=\"bookmark\">Chairperson to Embark on Outreach Visits to the Regions<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Pamela Mate The Chairperson of the National Council, Hon. Lukas Sinimbo Muha, will be conducting regional visits to the Otjozondjupa and Kavango East regions from Monday, 14 February to Saturday, 27 February 2022. The regional visits by the Office of the Chairperson forms part of Outreach Programme activities as set out in the National Council&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/chairperson-to-embark-on-outreach-visits-to-the-regions\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Chairperson to Embark on Outreach Visits to the Regions\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11113 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker wants public education on Constitution, 09\/02\/2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-wants-public-education-on-constitution-09-02-2022\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Constitution-2-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Constitution-2-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Constitution 2\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-wants-public-education-on-constitution-09-02-2022\/\" title=\"Speaker wants public education on Constitution, 09\/02\/2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker wants public education on Constitution, 09\/02\/2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; The Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi has suggested that civic education be held to inform and educate Namibian citizens about the purpose and importance of the constitution. Hon. Katjavivi said this in an interview with the media on Wednesday, (09\/02\/2022) during the marking of the&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-wants-public-education-on-constitution-09-02-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker wants public education on Constitution, 09\/02\/2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-11066 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Training for Budget Committee underway, 07\/02\/2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/training-for-budget-committee-underway\/\" title=\"Training for Budget Committee underway, 07\/02\/2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">Training for Budget Committee underway, 07\/02\/2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; Story by George Sanzila A three-day training workshop for the National Assembly Select Committee on budget focusing on public financial management, the budget process and oversight is currently underway. The workshop is organized in collaboration with the Enhancing Participatory Democracy in Namibia (EPDN) programme, which is a partnership programme of the European Union and&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/training-for-budget-committee-underway\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Training for Budget Committee underway, 07\/02\/2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-11051 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker implores managers to recommit themselves, 02\/02\/2022\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-implores-managers-to-recommit-themselves-02-02-2022\/\" title=\"Speaker implores managers to recommit themselves, 02\/02\/2022\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker implores managers to recommit themselves, 02\/02\/2022<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi in the company of his Deputy, Hon. Prof. Loide Kasingo addressed the management of the institution today (02\/02\/2022), in a meeting meant to set the tone for the year 2022 for the institution. The meeting was aimed at&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-implores-managers-to-recommit-themselves-02-02-2022\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker implores managers to recommit themselves, 02\/02\/2022\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-11033 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Council: 2021 in Review.\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-2021-in-review\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/Members-of-the-6th-National-Council-with-Right-Honourable-Prime-Minister-Saara-Kuugongelwa-Amadhila-and-His-Lordship-Peter-Shivute-after-their-swearing-in-scaled-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/Members-of-the-6th-National-Council-with-Right-Honourable-Prime-Minister-Saara-Kuugongelwa-Amadhila-and-His-Lordship-Peter-Shivute-after-their-swearing-in-scaled-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/Members-of-the-6th-National-Council-with-Right-Honourable-Prime-Minister-Saara-Kuugongelwa-Amadhila-and-His-Lordship-Peter-Shivute-after-their-swearing-in-scaled-1306x1306.jpg 1306w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Members of the 6th National Council with Right-Honourable Prime Minister, Saara Kuugongelwa-Amadhila and His Lordship Peter Shivute after their swearing in\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-2021-in-review\/\" title=\"National Council: 2021 in Review.\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Council: 2021 in Review.<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>National Council: 2021 in Review. The legislative business of the 6th National Council Chamber took place in the 1st to the 3rd Quarter in the financial Year ending 2021\/2022, during the period between 10 May to 09 December 2021. Amid the challenging times due to the global Covid 19 pandemic, the National Council held two&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-2021-in-review\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Council: 2021 in Review.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-11028 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Parliament Secretariat Meets to Discuss Collaboration with CSOs\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliament-secretariat-meets-to-discuss-collaboration-with-csos\/\" title=\"Parliament Secretariat Meets to Discuss Collaboration with CSOs\" rel=\"bookmark\">Parliament Secretariat Meets to Discuss Collaboration with CSOs<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Pamela Mate &nbsp; A meeting between Civil Society Organizations (CSOs) and Parliament took place today (24 January 2022), aimed as discussing collaboration between the two entities in Parliament\u2019s role of oversight of public policies and programmes. In her introductory remarks, Secretary to the National Assembly, Ms. Lydia Kandetu, underscored the need for such engagements, noting&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/parliament-secretariat-meets-to-discuss-collaboration-with-csos\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Parliament Secretariat Meets to Discuss Collaboration with CSOs\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-10985 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Hon Sirombo sworn in as MP in National Assembly\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/hon-sirombo-sworn-in-as-mp-in-national-assembly\/\" title=\"Hon Sirombo sworn in as MP in National Assembly\" rel=\"bookmark\">Hon Sirombo sworn in as MP in National Assembly<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Hon. Maria Sirombo of All People\u2019s Party (APP) was sworn in today (15\/12\/21) as a Member of Parliament in the National Assembly by Judge Sylvester Mainga. Her appointment follows the passing of the late APP President, Hon. Ignatius Shixwameni.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/hon-sirombo-sworn-in-as-mp-in-national-assembly\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Hon Sirombo sworn in as MP in National Assembly\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-10966 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Urban and Rural Development Minister Briefs MPs on Status of CDF Bill\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/urban-and-rural-development-minister-briefs-mps-on-status-of-cdf-bill\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20581%20581&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Urban-Briefing-2-581x581.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Urban-Briefing-2-581x581.jpg 581w\" alt=\"\" title=\"MURD Briefing\" width=\"581\" height=\"581\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/urban-and-rural-development-minister-briefs-mps-on-status-of-cdf-bill\/\" title=\"Urban and Rural Development Minister Briefs MPs on Status of CDF Bill\" rel=\"bookmark\">Urban and Rural Development Minister Briefs MPs on Status of CDF Bill<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Pamela Mate The Minister of Urban and Rural Development, Hon. Erastus Uutoni, yesterday (7 December 2021) briefed Members of the National Council on the status of the Constituency Development Fund Bill, commonly referred to as the CDF Bill. The Minister informed the Members that consultations by the Cabinet Committee on Treasury had been concluded and&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/urban-and-rural-development-minister-briefs-mps-on-status-of-cdf-bill\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Urban and Rural Development Minister Briefs MPs on Status of CDF Bill\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-10957 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Council Inaugurates New Members\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-inaugurates-new-members\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20750%20750&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/swearing-in-750x750.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/swearing-in-750x750.jpg 750w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Swearing in\" width=\"750\" height=\"750\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-inaugurates-new-members\/\" title=\"National Council Inaugurates New Members\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Council Inaugurates New Members<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Pamela Mate The National Council this week (29 November 2021) inaugurated two new Members. The new Members of Parliament are Hon. Kosmas Kayayuka Katura from the Musese Constituency in the Kavango East region and Hon. Bennety Likukela Busihu from Kongoloa Constituency in the Zambezi region. The Members replaced the late Katima Mulilo Urban Constituency Councillor&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-inaugurates-new-members\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Council Inaugurates New Members\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-10901 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"ATI Bill under scrutiny\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/ati-bill-under-scrutiny\/\" title=\"ATI Bill under scrutiny\" rel=\"bookmark\">ATI Bill under scrutiny<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; The Action Namibia Coalition submitted its input on the Access to Information Bill (ATI) during a public hearing conducted by the Parliamentary Standing Committee on Information and Communication Technology today (29\/11\/2021). Action Namibia Coalition is a grouping of activists, civil society and media organizations advocating for a comprehensive ATI&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/ati-bill-under-scrutiny\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about ATI Bill under scrutiny\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-10879 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Council Stakeholder Engagement Highlights Importance of Oversight Function\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-stakeholder-engagement-highlights-importance-of-oversight-function\/\" title=\"National Council Stakeholder Engagement Highlights Importance of Oversight Function\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Council Stakeholder Engagement Highlights Importance of Oversight Function<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Pamela Mate This week, Members of the 6th National Council are meeting key stakeholders in efforts to strengthen cooperation, highlight key issues and deepen consultation and communication between the Standing Committees of the National Council and Government Ministries, Agencies and Organizations (OMAs). The engagement is being held under the theme: Reflections on Oversight Framework. Speaking&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-stakeholder-engagement-highlights-importance-of-oversight-function\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Council Stakeholder Engagement Highlights Importance of Oversight Function\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-10850 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker impressed with Parliament&#8217;s digital transformation efforts, 13 November 2021\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-impressed-with-parliaments-digital-transformation-efforts-13-november-2021\/\" title=\"Speaker impressed with Parliament&#8217;s digital transformation efforts, 13 November 2021\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker impressed with Parliament&#8217;s digital transformation efforts, 13 November 2021<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi has thanked the World Bank for its continuous support in the legislature\u2019s quest for digital transformation. The Speaker met the World Bank Country Director, Marie Marie Nelly recently to gauge progress made thus far with regards to the e-parliament strategy.&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-impressed-with-parliaments-digital-transformation-efforts-13-november-2021\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker impressed with Parliament&#8217;s digital transformation efforts, 13 November 2021\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-10834 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker pays tribute to Shixwameni, 12 November 2021\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-pays-tribute-to-shixwameni-12-november-2021\/\" title=\"Speaker pays tribute to Shixwameni, 12 November 2021\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker pays tribute to Shixwameni, 12 November 2021<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; Windhoek &#8211; The Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi visited the widow of the late member of parliament, Hon. Ignatius Shiwameni to offer his condolences on behalf of the National Assembly. Hon. Shiwameni died on Wednesday during a committee meeting at parliament. Hon. Katjavivi noted that the National Assembly is saddened&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-pays-tribute-to-shixwameni-12-november-2021\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker pays tribute to Shixwameni, 12 November 2021\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-10794 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Indian High Commissioner meets Speaker, 09 November 2021\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/indian-high-commissioner-meets-speaker-09-november-2021\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/ind_del-1-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/ind_del-1-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"ind_del\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/indian-high-commissioner-meets-speaker-09-november-2021\/\" title=\"Indian High Commissioner meets Speaker, 09 November 2021\" rel=\"bookmark\">Indian High Commissioner meets Speaker, 09 November 2021<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Indian High Commissioner to Namibia, H.E. Prashant Agrawal visited the Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi today (09\/11\/21). The two exchanged views on the envisioned Namibian Parliament museum. The Speaker noted that the museum, which he says would encompass artefacts and an interactive digital display of information, was important in terms of&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/indian-high-commissioner-meets-speaker-09-november-2021\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Indian High Commissioner meets Speaker, 09 November 2021\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-10808 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Committee on Economics engages NRSC, 10 November 2021\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/committee-on-economics-engages-nrsc-10-november-2021\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/econo-1-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/econo-1-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"econo\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/committee-on-economics-engages-nrsc-10-november-2021\/\" title=\"Committee on Economics engages NRSC, 10 November 2021\" rel=\"bookmark\">Committee on Economics engages NRSC, 10 November 2021<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Windhoek &#8211; The Chairperson of the National Road Safety Council (NRSC), Elifas !Owos-Oab says the fragmentation of road safety management is hampering efforts to properly manage safety on Namibian roads. !Owos \u2013Oab said this in response to concerns raised by the Parliamentary Standing Committee on Economics and Public Administration during a consultative meeting today (10\/11\/21).&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/committee-on-economics-engages-nrsc-10-november-2021\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Committee on Economics engages NRSC, 10 November 2021\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-10802 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-media-releases category-news category-159 category-76 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"PASSING ON OF HONOURABLE IGNATIUS SHIXWAMENI, 10 NOVEMBER 2021\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/passing-on-of-honourable-ignatius-shixwameni-10-vovember-2021\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/late_shixwameni-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/late_shixwameni-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"late_shixwameni\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/passing-on-of-honourable-ignatius-shixwameni-10-vovember-2021\/\" title=\"PASSING ON OF HONOURABLE IGNATIUS SHIXWAMENI, 10 NOVEMBER 2021\" rel=\"bookmark\">PASSING ON OF HONOURABLE IGNATIUS SHIXWAMENI, 10 NOVEMBER 2021<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/documents\/media-releases\/\" >Media Releases<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The National Assembly, with permission from the family of Hon Ignatius Shixwameni, hereby confirm that Hon. Ignatius Shixwameni passed on today, Wednesday 10 November 2021, at Parliament. Read More >>><\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/passing-on-of-honourable-ignatius-shixwameni-10-vovember-2021\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about PASSING ON OF HONOURABLE IGNATIUS SHIXWAMENI, 10 NOVEMBER 2021\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-10748 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Assembly hosts Public Engagement on \u201cTackling Climate Change in Namibia\u201d\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/assembly-hosts-public-engagement-on-tackling-climate-change-in-namibia\/\" title=\"Assembly hosts Public Engagement on \u201cTackling Climate Change in Namibia\u201d\" rel=\"bookmark\">Assembly hosts Public Engagement on \u201cTackling Climate Change in Namibia\u201d<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by Rafael Hangula WINDHOEK- The Parliamentary Standing Committee on Natural Resources in collaboration with Hanns Seidel Foundation (HSF), held a Parliamentary-Public Engagement on \u201cTackling Climate Change in Namibia \u2013 Forestry as a Key Sector\u201d today (02\/11\/2021) at Parliament. It is the second engagement on natural resource management that the National Assembly has organised in&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/assembly-hosts-public-engagement-on-tackling-climate-change-in-namibia\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Assembly hosts Public Engagement on \u201cTackling Climate Change in Namibia\u201d\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-10729 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"APRM National secretariat pays courtesy call on Speaker\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/aprm-national-secretariat-pays-courtesy-call-on-speaker\/\" title=\"APRM National secretariat pays courtesy call on Speaker\" rel=\"bookmark\">APRM National secretariat pays courtesy call on Speaker<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; The African Peer Review Mechanism (APRM) National Secretariat visited the Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi on Wednesday, 27 October 2021. The secretariat, led by its Chief Executive Officer, Ambassador Lineekela Mboti informed the Speaker that a team of reviewers from the continental body will&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/aprm-national-secretariat-pays-courtesy-call-on-speaker\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about APRM National secretariat pays courtesy call on Speaker\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-10705 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-latest-added-documents category-media-releases category-news category-219 category-76 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Media Invitation: Public Hearing with the Ministry of Environment, Tourism and Forestry, 26 October 2021\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/media-invitation-public-hearing-with-the-ministry-of-environment-tourism-and-forestry-26-october-2021\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/media_logo-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/media_logo-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"media_logo\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/media-invitation-public-hearing-with-the-ministry-of-environment-tourism-and-forestry-26-october-2021\/\" title=\"Media Invitation: Public Hearing with the Ministry of Environment, Tourism and Forestry, 26 October 2021\" rel=\"bookmark\">Media Invitation: Public Hearing with the Ministry of Environment, Tourism and Forestry, 26 October 2021<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/latest-added-documents\/\" >Latest Added Documents<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/documents\/media-releases\/\" >Media Releases<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The Parliamentary Standing Committee on Natural Resources, as part of its oversight functions will hold a public hearing with the Ministry of Environment, Tourism and Forestry. Read More &gt;&gt;&gt;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/media-invitation-public-hearing-with-the-ministry-of-environment-tourism-and-forestry-26-october-2021\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Media Invitation: Public Hearing with the Ministry of Environment, Tourism and Forestry, 26 October 2021\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-10693 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Clerks-at-the-Table Seminar, Nairobi, Kenya\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/clerks-at-the-table-seminar-nairobi-kenya\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/socatt-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/socatt-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"socatt\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/clerks-at-the-table-seminar-nairobi-kenya\/\" title=\"Clerks-at-the-Table Seminar, Nairobi, Kenya\" rel=\"bookmark\">Clerks-at-the-Table Seminar, Nairobi, Kenya<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The Secretaries of Parliament is attending the Society of Clerks at the Table Seminar in Nairobi, Kenya. The seminar is held under the theme \u201cPromoting adaptive programming in Parliamentary settings as a response to emergency and emerging global, regional and national challenges\u201d. The Society of Clerks-at-the-Table of the Commonwealth Parliaments (SoCATT) was founded in 1932&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/clerks-at-the-table-seminar-nairobi-kenya\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Clerks-at-the-Table Seminar, Nairobi, Kenya\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-10654 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Natural Resources Committee Consults Ministry of Mines on Recon Africa activities, 12 October 2021\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/natural-resources-committee-consults-ministry-of-mines-on-recon-africa-activities-12-october-2021\/\" title=\"Natural Resources Committee Consults Ministry of Mines on Recon Africa activities, 12 October 2021\" rel=\"bookmark\">Natural Resources Committee Consults Ministry of Mines on Recon Africa activities, 12 October 2021<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; The Parliamentary Standing Committee on Natural Resources held a consultative meeting with the Ministry of Mines and Energy today (12\/10\/2021). The meeting, prompted by a petition opposed to Recon Africa oil and gas exploration activities in the Kavango regions, follows a recent fact finding mission by the Committee to&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/natural-resources-committee-consults-ministry-of-mines-on-recon-africa-activities-12-october-2021\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Natural Resources Committee Consults Ministry of Mines on Recon Africa activities, 12 October 2021\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-10622 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"National Council Standing Committee Conducts Oversight Meetings in Zambezi Region\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-standing-committee-conducts-oversight-meetings-in-zambezi-region\/\" title=\"National Council Standing Committee Conducts Oversight Meetings in Zambezi Region\" rel=\"bookmark\">National Council Standing Committee Conducts Oversight Meetings in Zambezi Region<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/administratorparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>By: Pamela Mate The National Council Standing Committee on Home Affairs, Security, Constitutional and Legal Affairs (HASCLA) conducted public meetings in the Zambezi Region with communities living along the Chobe, Kwando and Linyanti rivers to assess the security situation, livelihood and tourism in those areas in the backdrop of alleged hostilities by members of the&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-standing-committee-conducts-oversight-meetings-in-zambezi-region\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about National Council Standing Committee Conducts Oversight Meetings in Zambezi Region\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-10613 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Condolence Message from National Council for the passing on of  Hon. Sikondo\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/condolence-message-from-national-council-for-the-passing-on-of-hon-sikondo\/\" title=\"Condolence Message from National Council for the passing on of  Hon. Sikondo\" rel=\"bookmark\">Condolence Message from National Council for the passing on of  Hon. Sikondo<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>The National Council has learned with great sadness about the sudden death of the late Hon Johannes Kahonzo Sikondo after a short illness on Sunday, the 19th of September 2021. The message was devastating, because the Late Sikondo was both a colleague of mine at the National Council and the Kavango West Regional Council. Read&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/condolence-message-from-national-council-for-the-passing-on-of-hon-sikondo\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Condolence Message from National Council for the passing on of  Hon. Sikondo\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-10594 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"PAC probes the financial intelligence unit, 30 September 2021\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/pac-probes-the-financial-intelligence-unit-30-september-2021\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20600%20600&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/fic1-600x600.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/fic1-600x600.jpg 600w\" alt=\"\" title=\"fic1\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/pac-probes-the-financial-intelligence-unit-30-september-2021\/\" title=\"PAC probes the financial intelligence unit, 30 September 2021\" rel=\"bookmark\">PAC probes the financial intelligence unit, 30 September 2021<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; The Parliamentary Standing Committee on Public Accounts was briefed by the Financial Intelligence Centre (FIC) on its roles and responsibilities today (30\/09\/2021). The meeting is part of a series of consultative meetings with different stakeholders meant to understand their roles in order to empower the committee to conduct its&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/pac-probes-the-financial-intelligence-unit-30-september-2021\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about PAC probes the financial intelligence unit, 30 September 2021\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-10559 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"MPs attend training on Governance and Sustainable Development Agenda\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/mps-attend-training-on-governance-and-sustainable-development-agenda\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20768%20768&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Training-in-otjiwarongo-24-26-September-2021-1-768x768.jpg\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Training-in-otjiwarongo-24-26-September-2021-1-768x768.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Training-in-otjiwarongo-24-26-September-2021-1.jpg 1080w\" alt=\"\" title=\"Training in otjiwarongo 24-26 September 2021\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/mps-attend-training-on-governance-and-sustainable-development-agenda\/\" title=\"MPs attend training on Governance and Sustainable Development Agenda\" rel=\"bookmark\">MPs attend training on Governance and Sustainable Development Agenda<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>&nbsp; WINDHOEK- Members of Parliament from both Houses (National Assembly and National Council) recently attended a training on Governance and Sustainable Development Agenda, in Otjiwarongo. The workshop aimed at empowering MPs to appreciate the meaning and value of public Governance; the centrality of accountability and ethics to public governance, amongst others. Parliaments and parliamentarians have&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/mps-attend-training-on-governance-and-sustainable-development-agenda\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about MPs attend training on Governance and Sustainable Development Agenda\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-10485 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"Speaker implores parliaments to advance democracy\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-implores-parliaments-to-advance-democracy\/\" title=\"Speaker implores parliaments to advance democracy\" rel=\"bookmark\">Speaker implores parliaments to advance democracy<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi has urged parliaments across the world to continue to advance the values of democracy in order to improve the livelihood of people. Hon. Katjavivi mentioned this today, in an online conference on the International Day of democracy which is being&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-implores-parliaments-to-advance-democracy\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about Speaker implores parliaments to advance democracy\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden no-img post-10470 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-home-page-slider category-news category-159 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"MPs engage in climate change mitigation efforts\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/mps-engage-in-climate-change-mitigation-efforts\/\" title=\"MPs engage in climate change mitigation efforts\" rel=\"bookmark\">MPs engage in climate change mitigation efforts<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/home-page-slider\/\" >Home-page Slider<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/hangulamexigmail-com\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Story by George Sanzila &nbsp; Windhoek &#8211; Members of Parliament from the Parliamentary Standing committee on Natural Resources and the committee on Economics and Public Administration undertook site visits to various renewable and eco-friendly initiatives within the vicinity of Windhoek yesterday (13\/09\/2021). The visits are part of a project aimed at raising awareness about the&hellip;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/mps-engage-in-climate-change-mitigation-efforts\/\" class=\"post-details details-type-link\" aria-label=\"Read more about MPs engage in climate change mitigation efforts\" rel=\"nofollow\">Read article<i class=\"dt-icon-the7-arrow-03\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\n<\/div><\/article><article class=\"post project-odd hidden post-10460 type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-latest-added-documents category-media-releases category-news category-219 category-76 category-39 description-off\" data-name=\"RESPONSE TO AN EDITORIAL OF THE NAMIBIAN NEWSPAPER: \u201cA dangerous precedent\u201d\" data-date=\"\">\n\n<div class=\"post-thumbnail-wrap\">\n\t<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/response-to-an-editorial-of-the-namibian-newspaper-a-dangerous-precedent\/\" class=\"post-thumbnail-rollover layzr-bg layzr-bg\" ><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"blog-thumb-lazy-load preload-me lazy-load\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D&#39;http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg&#39;%20viewBox%3D&#39;0%200%20300%20300&#39;%2F%3E\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/pdf-logo.png\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/pdf-logo.png 300w\" alt=\"\" title=\"pdf-logo\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\"  \/><\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"post-entry-content\">\n\n\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\">\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/response-to-an-editorial-of-the-namibian-newspaper-a-dangerous-precedent\/\" title=\"RESPONSE TO AN EDITORIAL OF THE NAMIBIAN NEWSPAPER: \u201cA dangerous precedent\u201d\" rel=\"bookmark\">RESPONSE TO AN EDITORIAL OF THE NAMIBIAN NEWSPAPER: \u201cA dangerous precedent\u201d<\/a>\n\t<\/h3>\n\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\"><span class=\"category-link\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/latest-added-documents\/\" >Latest Added Documents<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/documents\/media-releases\/\" >Media Releases<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/category\/news\/\" >News<\/a><\/span><a class=\"author vcard\" href=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/author\/e-angulaparliament-na\/\" title=\"View all posts by \" rel=\"author\">By <span class=\"fn\"><\/span><\/a><\/div>\n\t<div class=\"entry-excerpt\"><p>Media Release 13 September 2021 RESPONSE TO AN EDITORIAL OF THE NAMIBIAN NEWSPAPER: \u201cA dangerous precedent\u201d We respond to the editorial in the Friday 10 September 2021 edition of The Namibian with the heading \u201cA Dangerous Precedent\u201d. The National Assembly wants to put the record straight as follows. Read More<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\n<a href=\"https:\/\/ww